title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients except nuts in large bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until chips are melted, 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased square baking dish, 8 x 8-inches.
Refrigerate until set.

title: bubbling jade punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients and chill. Makes 20 (4 ounce) servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix and set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl, then pour in the pie shells and refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving. Keep what is left in the refrigerator.

title: sausage roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 425° or until brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Put the cornbread mix in a bowl, then mix with the ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°, then put the cornbread in a pan and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 15 minutes. This sauce can be used on chicken or ribs.

title: camembert french bread
directions: Combine cheese, butter, basil and onion salt.
Simmer over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool for 10 minutes until starts to thicken, stirring occasionally.
Slice bread lengthwise.
Spread some of the cheese mixture on cut surfaces. Put loaf together and spread remaining cheese mixture on top and sides.
Wrap in foil and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Turn back foil and bake for 5 more minutes.
Slice to serve.

title: hormel chili dip
directions: Heat slowly all ingredients while stirring until hot.
Serve with chips.

title: one-bowl brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl at High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into melted chocolate until well blended.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until completely mixed.
Mix in flour until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out almost clean (do not overbake).
Cool in pan; cut into squares.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: apricot granola muffins
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in milk and almond extract.
In another bowl, mix flours, baking powder, cinnamon, granola and apricots.
Add to butter mixture and beat until just moistened.
Divide batter among 12 large greased or lined muffin cups.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: grantham gingerbreads
directions: Whisk butter and sugar together in a bowl until pale and fluffy.
Gradually beating the egg, sift the flour and ginger into the mixture and work in with a fork until fairly firm dough is obtained.
Roll dough into small balls, about size of walnut, and put them on buttered baking sheets, spaced apart.
Bake in the oven at 150° Centigrade, 300° Fahrenheit or gas mark 2 for 40 to 45 minutes, until crisp, well risen, hollow and very lightly browned.

title: ginger-almond tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; cover and steep 5 minutes. Remove tea bags, squeezing gently.
Stir in sugar and next 4 ingredients; chill.
Stir in ginger ale before serving.
Make 3 quarts.

title: mom's party beans
directions: Mix in all ingredients to taste and bring to a boil. Simmer for 45 minutes to an hour until sauce has thickened and flavors have mixed.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Mix eggs and spices.
Slowly add hot milk.
Pour into pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients with large fork and chill.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix with electric beater.
A little more milk may be added, if necessary.
Top the top layer of graham crackers with icing.
Cover with aluminum foil and place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Cut into squares and store in covered container in refrigerator.
Freezes quite well.

title: casserole of corn
directions: Fry bacon until lightly crisp.
Break into bits.
Mix bacon with milk and bread crumbs.
Stir into corn with salt, chili powder, cheese and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until puffy and creamy soft. Garnish with additional crumbled bacon.

title: smothered fresh corn
directions: Saute onions in oil until brown, about 10 minutes. Add 1/4 cup water and cook for 5 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce and simmer 20 minutes. Add 1/2 cup water and cook for 10 minutes. Add corn, water, sugar and salt. Cook for about 40 minutes. Add pepper to taste.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch square pan or 1 1/4-quart baking dish. Pour blueberries into pan.
Combine sugar, orange rind, cardamon and mace.
Sprinkle sugar mixture and pie crust mix in alternate layers over blueberries.
Continue until all is used.
Dot with butter.
Drizzle lemon juice and vanilla over all.
Bake for 45 minutes, until bubbly and topping is lightly browned.
Serve with heavy cream.

title: peanut pudding cake
directions: Layer 1:
In small bowl, thoroughly mix 2/3 cup chopped peanuts, flour and softened butter.
Press into bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding, oil and water.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sour cream, chocolate chips, walnuts and grated German chocolate.
Add coconut.
Put in greased tube cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: easy oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Shake chicken pieces until coated.
Arrange skin side down in butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes; turn and bake 25 more minutes.

title: spiced peanuts
directions: Boil sugar, water and spices until syrup threads from spoon (293°).
Drop peanuts into syrup.
Stir until nuts are dry looking.
Pour out on waxed paper and let stand until cold and dry.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Mix Italian dressing and chicken breasts in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Make rice as directed and serve chicken breasts with Italian dressing over rice.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes.
Prick with a fork.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Cut a lengthwise slice from top of each baked potato; discard skin from slice and place pulp in bowl.
Gently scoop out each potato, leaving a thin shell. Add pulp to bowl.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 inch baking dish (glass works well). In bowl, combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, and salt; add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour batter over butter. (Do not stir.) Bring remaining 1 cup sugar, peach or other fruit slices and lemon juice to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Pour over batter. (Do not stir.) Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg. Bake at 375° for 40 - 45 minutes or until brown.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add rice, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour into well-greased casserole. Bake for about 1 hour, or until mixture does not adhere to a knife.

title: carol's chicken casserole
directions: Combine
soups and broth; set aside.
Place 1 box of dry stuffing mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Place
half the cubed chicken and half the soup/broth mixture. Repeat. Bake until bubbly, about 45 minutes in a 375° oven. Suitable for large group as it serves several.

title: snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; may vary it with other ingredients.

title: easy chicken-pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Mix egg, milk, oil and salt together.
Add flour until dough is stiff enough to roll.
Roll on floured board and cook in boiling broth.

title: cabbage and bow ties
directions: Cook bow ties (or other shapes) according to package directions.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine until clear. Slice cabbage very thinly and add to onion.
Continue cooking on medium heat until cabbage wilts.
Add the cooked and drained pasta along with 1 to 2 tablespoons butter in small slices.
Continue cooking and stirring until heated through.
Top with grated Parmesan.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Beat egg whites with dash of salt until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Mash cranberries with fork.
Whip the cream.
Add flavoring.
Fold all together.
Pour in dish.
Cover.
Put in freezer.
Take out of freezer 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: In a large kettle, bring to a boil over medium heat for a long time until 232° or firm ball stage in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir and then add 2 cups pecans.
Drop on buttered foil.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cut vegetables in bite-size pieces. Place all vegetables, except avocados, in a large mixing or storage bowl. Cover vegetables with Italian dressing and refrigerate for at least 4 to 8 hours (can make in the morning to serve at dinner).
Stir vegetables to mix dressing. Place in serving bowl and add bite-sized pieces of avocado and serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In small bowl, cook onion in small amount of water; set aside. Cook broccoli (without salt) in water until tender.
In large bowl (at least 3-quart), soften Velveeta in microwave.
Add onion and water, condensed milk, slightly drained broccoli and enough whole milk to make about 2 1/2 quarts in bowl.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Add flour and water mixture and cook until soup thickens.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix sugar, pickling spice, vinegar and salt.
Put cucumbers in jar and pour boiling water over them.
Let stand 24 hours.
Repeat 3 other times, draining and pouring boiling water over cucumbers each day.
On day 5, drain and let stand 48 hours.
Bring to boil and seal in jars.

title: the sparma's special spaghetti sauce
directions: Place tomato sauce, tomato paste and spices into a crock-pot or large saucepan on low for 3 to 6 hours.
One hour before serving, add meatballs and pepperoni, sliced thick.
Remove onion. Serve over cooked pasta of your choice.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramelized popcorn balls
directions: Pop popcorn; mix with peanuts in a large bowl.
Cook syrup, molasses, butter and vinegar in a saucepan, stirring occasionally to hard ball stage (250° on candy thermometer).
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Toss together with forks.
Shape into balls and cool.

title: colina's cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, flour and baking powder well.
Pour half of batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Add cocoa and swirl into batter.
Pour in remaining mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat the eggs in a medium mixing bowl until very thick and lemon colored.
Add the milk gradually, then add the bacon drippings and blend thoroughly.
Add the flour and salt gradually and beat until smooth.
Fold in half the cheese.
Pour into a well-greased 1-quart baking dish.
Then sprinkle the remaining cheese over top.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
This makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turkey burgers(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 4 patties.
Broil about 6 minutes on each side until cooked.
Serve on sesame rolls with lettuce and any condiments you choose.

title: mel's pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugars, Karos, butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli potato soup
directions: Put soup in big pot and dilute with 1 can milk and 1 can water. Add spices.
Next add potatoes and broccoli.
Cook for 5 minutes. Last, add cheese and cook 10 additional minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: molly cray's lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix the sugar, butter and beaten egg yolks.
Add the juice and grated rind of lemon, flour, milk and the whites of the 2 eggs (beaten stiff).
Bake at 325° or 350°, depending on your oven, for 3/4 hour.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add water or coffee and cocoa. Mix well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix this stiff batter well and slowly add 1 cup of very hot water. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° until top springs back.
This is a very moist cake.

title: mari's cheese potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt the butter, then saute the onions in the butter until translucent.
Add the cheese and parsley and stir until the cheese melts.
Add potatoes and coat with cheese.
Can be served as is or placed in oven to brown the cheese on top of the potatoes.

title: delicious and tender steak and gravy
directions: In large pot, mix soups together. Stir in water and mushrooms. Cut steak in single servings. Add to soup mix.
Cover and simmer 3 hours. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: nita's fruit cake
directions: Boil marshmallows and milk.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Use your hand to finish.
Wet hand to finish cake to make it shine.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat uncooked ground beef in pan or dish.
Sprinkle onion on top of meat and smooth undiluted soup over all.
Layer Tater Tots on top and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix Well.
Pour over 6 cups sliced cucumbers (unpeeled), 1 cup sliced onions (purple and white), 1 cup green peppers.
If you do not like "sweet" pickles; omit the sugar and add 1 cup salt for a zesty taste.

title: maine fish soup
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Simmer until hot.
Stir often.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Put into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° for 20 minutes covered.
Bake an additional 10 minutes uncovered.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: tuna nicoise pasta
directions: Rinse potato and green beans; cut potato in 2 cubes.
Snap green beans in 2-inch lengths and discard stems.
Put vegetables in large skillet with broth and thyme.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover; simmer 8 minutes.
While they are simmering, chop parsley and add tuna.
Slice olives; add to bowl along with vegetables and broth.
To serve, toss hot pasta.
Cut lemon in half.
Squeeze juice over pasta and toss again.
Season with pepper.
Serves 5.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in sauce.
When chicken is throughly cooked, remove from pan.
With vegetables make a large tossed salad.
Add any fresh salad vegetable you like.
Toss in pineapple and walnuts.
On individual dinner plates, place tossed salad. Top with chicken.
Use your favorite salad dressing.

title: cole slaw
directions: Put salad
oil,
vinegar,
salt and sugar in a saucepan and bring to
a
boil.	Pour over vegetables and let set until cool. Mix well.
Put
in a jar and keep in fridge.
Will keep up to 3 weeks.
This
cole	slaw is very good and so handy to have on hand.

title: fig and nut bread
directions: Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Cream margarine until fluffy.
Beat in brown sugar and egg.
Stir in milk and vinegar.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually until well blended.
Add nuts and chopped figs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours, until firm in center.
Cool; remove from pan.
Slice real thin and serve with butter or whipped cream cheese.

title: party broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli
minutes
in
salted water.
Mix soup, sour cream,
rosemary and onions, sauteed.
Mix with broccoli. Top with bread
crumbs
browned in butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 12.

title: sunday rolls (icebox)
directions: Let milk, sugar and shortening come almost to a boil.
Let cool to lukewarm.
While cooling, add yeast to lukewarm water.
When 1st mixture is warm, add yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make a batter (like cake batter).
Set aside for 2 hours to let rise. Then add salt, baking powder, soda and enough flour make a dough that you can handle (not too much).
Put in large bowl and put in refrigerator or make rolls and let rise 2 hours before baking. Bake at 450° to 475° until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large pot, completely cover chicken with water.
Boil chicken until falling off bone.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: date cookies
directions: Combine dates, sugar, egg and butter.
Cook over low heat until dates are melted.
Remove from heat to cool; add vanilla, pecans and Rice Krispies.
Make into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and salt in small saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup water and vinegar.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and pecans.
Pour in mold. Chill until firm.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Butter cake dish (8 x 8-inch) generously.
Beat first 4 ingredients until very creamy.
Pour into glass dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool for 10 minutes.

title: aunt belle's cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo until soft, not brown. Blend in flour. Gradually stir in broth, then milk. Cook, stirring, until it thickens and boils. Stir in salt and cheese. Heat until cheese melts. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: lemon bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in flour and baking powder.
Pour over crust and bake 25 minutes at 325°. Cool, then cut in bars.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Stir in 1 cup milk and 1 (3 ounce) can broiled mushroom slices with liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add 1 tablespoon onion and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Spoon over ham puffs or other main dish just before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix orange jello and hot water.
Let stand until jello jells slightly.
Fold fruit into jello (let jell slightly).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and seasonings.
Drain.
Spread in a greased baking dish.
Blend milk, eggs and baking mix together and pour over beef.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes more until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes on wire rack.

title: beef brisket
directions: Salt brisket and sprinkle with garlic.
Trim excess fat and score.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix syrup, sugar, flour and butter.
Mix well. Add salt and vanilla.
Bake in deep uncooked pie shell at 400° until firm.

title: clam chowder
directions: Wash clams and chop with chopper.
Fry out salt pork with lard. Add water and cook for 2 hours.
Then, add vegetables and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and carrots.
Boil in water until tender. Strain, reserving 1 cup water.
In saucepan, saute onions in butter until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Serve hot and sprinkle with paprika.

title: butter creams
directions: Beat margarine, salt and extract.
Add milk and sugar; mix until smooth, not sticky.
Cover in chocolate.
Dip in wax.
You can use cinnamon instead of chocolate.

title: pizza meatloaf
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs.
Add 3/4 cup of pizza sauce, cheese, bread crumbs, garlic salt and pepper.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1-1/4 hours.
Drain.
Spoon remaining pizza sauce over meatloaf.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until no pink remains.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 6-8.

title: walnut pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until pie is set.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Heat oil in pan. Brown sausage, cooking thoroughly. Remove sausage from pan. Leave oil in pan and turn heat down. Add flour to oil until oil turns to a paste. Brown for 1 minute. Add milk gradually until paste turns to liquid, stirring constantly. Allow to thicken. Add more milk; continue allowing gravy to thicken. Add milk to desired texture. Stir constantly while cooking. Add spices. Goes great with homemade biscuits.

title: indian cabbage
directions: Place shredded cabbage, corned beef and onion in 4-quart casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Pour milk and butter over casserole.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook 30 minutes more, or until brown and cabbage is tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Use more moister if needed.

title: chicken ole
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, layer ingredients starting with tortillas.
I usually fry lightly in cooking oil to make them pliable.
Layer chicken, cheese, onions and soup. Repeat.
Final layer should be cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Blend together cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, bell pepper, onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add pimentos after other ingredients are thoroughly blended.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: fruit swirl
directions: Combine ingredients in blender and whirl until smooth.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut bread in cubes.
Combine eggs, milk, seasonings, onion and butter.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese in unbuttered casserole.
Pour liquid over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and 3/4 of Cool Whip together until smooth in mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Clean and cut strawberries into bite-size pieces.
Reserve some whole or halves for garnishing.
Mix glaze with strawberries until covered.
Spoon glazed strawberries on top of cream cheese-Cool Whip mixture. Spoon remaining Cool Whip over top of strawberry glaze mixture and spread.
Garnish with remaining strawberries.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Keep covered and refrigerated.
Makes 9-inch pie or 8 servings.

title: another potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on and eggs the night before; chill in refrigerator.
Chop all ingredients and mix well.
Blend salad dressing, mustard and horseradish in separate bowl.
Add dressing mixture to salad mixture and mix.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill and serve.
Serves 12.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Beat 1 egg and fill cup with milk (1 measuring cup).
Makes 5 or 6 crusts.

title: sausage casserole(brunch)
directions: Grease oblong pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Lay 6 pieces of bread on bottom of pan.
Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Mix mustard with browned sausage.
Spoon over bread.
Add cheese (grated) over sausage.
Beat eggs and half and half with Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cube steak casserole
directions: Mix in 2-quart casserole dish cubed steaks cut into bite-sizes, peas and soup.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake in microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: baked savory chicken
directions: Wash chicken parts and cut away excess fat and skin.
Place in a large Pyrex baking dish, as bottom layer.
Combine all remaining ingredients except almonds and cover all the chicken with this sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
In the last 15 minutes, sprinkle on the sliced almonds.
Add 1/4 cup bread crumbs, if desired. Return all to oven for 15 minutes more, until light brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: crawfish corn maquchoux
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine and add all
ingredients except crawfish.
Cook until corn is tender.
Add crawfish and cook about 10 minutes longer.

title: ranch house beans
directions: Brown hamburg in margarine.
Add onion soup mix, water, ketchup, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar in frypan.
Cook beans in crock-pot or pan.
Add hamburg mixture and simmer.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blend well.
Stir in mini chocolate chips.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping, chocolate shavings or fruit of desire.

title: rolled pork loin
directions: Blend all ingredients, except roast, together and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Place roast in a cooking bag along with the liquid mixture.
Cook at 250° for 4 hours.

title: easy apricot cobbler
directions: Put apricots in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Use 3/4 stick of margarine on top of fruit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix Bisquick and sugar together.
Put over the fruit.
Add rest of margarine to top of dry mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Blend together salad oil, vinegar, orange juice and salt.
Pour over chicken or turkey.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Put flour mixture into the sugar mix.
Make into size of walnuts.
Press with a glass with sugar.
(At Christmastime use the red and green sugars.)
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or less.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: eight minute light and fruity pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring for about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes (6) and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in whipped topping; whip until smooth. Fold in strawberries.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: mexican dish
directions: Line bottom of casserole with taco chips.
Cook hamburger, onions and remaining ingredients (except cheese).
Put in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch casserole baking dish.
Combine sugar and flour. Add milk and beaten eggs.
Stir in corn and melted butter from casserole dish.
Since butter is melted in baking dish, no other greasing is necessary.
Bake at 350° until custard is set and top is golden brown.

title: sam's baked ham
directions: Cover ham with aluminum foil.
Bake whole ham 3 1/4 to 3 1/2 hours or halve ham and bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
After 45 minutes, before baking time is up, remove from oven.
Take off rind and score.
Cut most of fat off.
Stud each square with whole clove.
Ham may be spread with paste of 1 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon dry mustard and 2 to 3 tablespoons of vinegar, honey or syrup.
Return to oven for 45 minutes.
Baste with fruit juice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda.
Mix in oil, cinnamon and eggs; add chopped apples.
Grease and flour three (9-inch) pans; divide dough among pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: low-fat bean and basil soup
directions: Bring stock to boil.
Add tomatoes, onion and oregano; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add beans; cook until onion is tender.
Add garlic, basil and oil.
With slotted spoon, remove half the beans and vegetables; puree until smooth.
Stir back into soup.
Cook pasta 6 minutes; drain and reserve 1 cup of cooking water.
Stir pasta into soup.
Add some reserved water if soup is too thick.

title: jalapeno jam
directions: Combine peppers and vinegar, half at a time, in blender. Puree until smooth.
Combine puree, sugar, salt and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil; cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add pectin.
Let stand for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add food coloring; mix well.
Pour into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 4 1/2 pint jars.

title: shrimp and corn soup
directions: Season shrimp and set aside.
Make roux of oil and flour.

Add onions and celery to roux and cook until onions are wilted, stirring occasionally. Add roux, corn, sliced lemon and ketchup to water and cook for about 25 minutes. Add shrimp and cook for another 15 minutes. Season to taste.
Add onion tops.
Let set a few minutes and serve in soup bowls.

title: bread sticky buns
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough overnight in refrigerator.
Grease bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tear 1 loaf into small pieces and cover bottom of pan.
In saucepan, melt oleo.
Add brown sugar, vanilla pudding, cinnamon and milk.
Mix and put on top of bread.
Break the other loaf and put on top of syrup. Cover and let stand at room temperature for 2 hours to rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best shrimp pie(my mother's, mrs. robert e. magwood)
directions: Fry bacon which has been cut up, remove meat, and chop green pepper, onion, celery.
Brown a little flour in bacon grease, adding enough water and flour to make a thick, brown gravy.
Add bacon, chopped ingredients, and cooked shrimp, salt and pepper to taste.
Let mixture simmer for a few minutes.
Pour a portion in a casserole, add layer of bread crumbs, and so on until the dish is filled.
Put a thick layer of bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake until brown.

title: hot rice
directions: Cook rice as directed; cool.
Boil chicken giblets; chop in small pieces. Boil eggs.
Fry sausage in small pieces.
Chop onion, green pepper and boiled eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve warm or cold.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add butter, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes and cut.

title: sally lund bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter; add sugar and eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Dissolve yeast in warm milk; add remaining milk.
Sift together salt and flour; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Cover and allow to stand in warm place until double (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and turn into a buttered ring mold or tube pan.
Cover until doubled (30 minutes).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out immediately onto wire rack to cool, right side up.
Drizzle with vanilla icing while still warm.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add lemonade, water, pineapple juice plus water.
Freeze solid.
Remove 3 hours before serving.
Crush as you can.
Add 2 liter bottles 7-Up.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add meat and cook until crumbly.
Add salt, pepper and chili pepper.
Mix together corn, tomatoes, olives, corn meal, milk and eggs.
Then add to meat and other ingredients.
Pour entire mixture into large, flat greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not cook until it is dry, just nicely brown.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and sweetener in bowl and stir in seed.
Add milk with spoon and knead by hand until well mixed.
Roll into balls and serve.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in oblong pan. Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and milk. Pour over butter. Mix cocoa and 3/4 cup sugar. Sprinkle over flour mixture. Slowly drizzle water over this. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well rice, soup, onions and cheese spread.
Pour layer into well-greased baking dish. Put layer of broccoli, then pour in remaining mixed ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets and rinse.
Add to boiling, salted water and cook, covered, for about 5 minutes. Drain.
Melt butter, add flour and blend well.
Gradually add milk and remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Place drained cauliflower in casserole, pour sauce over top. Sprinkle crumbs over all and bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
This is also good using half cauliflower and half broccoli.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pot-roasted beef dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel a strip around tiny potatoes. If using medium potatoes, cut in chunks.
Lightly spray an unheated Dutch oven with no-stick spray.
Add the meat and brown. Drain drippings from pan.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar in 1/4 cup warm water. Add yeast mixture to remaining ingredients.
Let rise 2 hours in a warm place.
Shape into rolls.
No kneading necessary.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan (greased and floured) or 60 minutes in greased and floured tube cake pan.

title: garlic bubble bread
directions: Thaw a loaf of frozen white bread. Mix remaining ingredients together. Cool mixture and add 1 beaten egg.
Cut the bread into small pieces and dip into the mixture.
Place in greased loaf pan. Let rise. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes until brown.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients and lemon juice or vinegar.
Add salad oil slowly, beating constantly, until thick.
If desired, honey may be substituted for sugar.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and chop shrimp.
Add other ingredients, then horseradish to taste.
Mix well; let stand at least 4 hours to enhance flavor.

title: cod or haddock italian style
directions: Cut fish into 3 servings; sprinkle with salt.
Place in greased oven-glass pie pan.
Pour tomato sauce and lemon juice over fish, sprinkle with cheese and dot with bits of margarine.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until fish flakes and cheese has browned lightly, about 25 minutes.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Heat liquid to boiling.
Add lemon jello.
Mix until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce; stir until well blended.
Stir in ginger ale.
Chill until consistency of egg white.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Spoon into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, cheese, eggs, pepper, pickles, olives, onion and mayonnaise or salad dressing. Spread about 1/3 cup onto each bun. Wrap each sandwich in wax paper. Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds (per sandwich) or until cheese melts. Yield: 6 servings.

title: pine-o-frost drink
directions: Put all ingredients except ice cubes in a blender.
Blend for 30 seconds, adding 1 ice cube at a time until smooth.
Very nutritious.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients and make into meat balls.
Roll balls in bread crumbs.
Put in pan that has been greased with 2 to 3 tablespoons oil.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: tender homemade noodles
directions: Put the flour in a bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Mix until the mixture forms a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board until very thin.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up and slice into strips; shake out and let dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling chicken broth or beef bouillon.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 36 cups liquid.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: english toffee(microwave)
directions: Combine butter, sugar, corn syrup and water in 2-quart glass mixing 'n pour bowl.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 4 minutes. Stir.
Microwave on High uncovered for 6 to 8 minutes until 300° is reached.
(I find it takes longer), stirring and checking temperature during last few minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour onto ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Let stand until chocolate is softened; spread over toffee.
Sprinkle with nuts, pressing them into chocolate.
Refrigerate to set chocolate.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Cook over low heat and stir until you have play dough consistency.
Store in zip plastic bag or margarine tub.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all together and stir to mix.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In large pot, saute butter and onion.
Cut up vegetables and add to butter and onion.
Cook, covered, until done.
Put vegetables in large casserole; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve and enjoy.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: "ma" esther's hermit cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs
first,
then add vanilla, lemon juice and cinnamon. Sift flour into a large pan and cut dates into the flour. Add batter to floured dates. Add	nuts and
mix well.
Bake in a lightly greased
tube
or Bundt pan for 2 to 2 1/4 hours at 250°.
Test with a straw.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix orange juice, jello and boiling water together.
Let sit until soupy.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Let jell.

title: strawberry and cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread in crust.
Refrigerate.
Mix Jell-O, pudding mix and water in medium saucepan until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in strawberries. Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 500°. Melt 3/4 stick butter in cookie sheet on 2 burners on top of stove. Slice peeled apples thinly into melted butter. Cook until transparent. Mix milk, flour, eggs, sugar and salt. Pour batter over apples. Place in oven. When cake has raised (about 5 minutes), remove from oven and powder with cinnamon and sugar and dot with remaining butter. Return to oven to brown (another 5 minutes). Cut into squares to serve. Sprinkle with lemon juice before eating.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease loaf pan and flour lightly.
Preheat oven to 325°. Mash bananas.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake 45 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: chicken or steak fajita
directions: Marinate chicken or
steak
hours in Fajita Marinade (see recipe).
Char-broil
chicken
or
steak
and
slice into 2-inch strips.
Stir-fry in olive oil an equal amount of onion and green pepper
strips
with
an
equal amount of chicken or steak strips. Mixture
should be hot with vegetables crunchy. Heat 6 flour tortillas
in a plastic Ziploc bag in a microwave oven until warm (do not overcook).	Pour stir-fry mixture on a hot platter and serve
immediately.
Squeeze lime halves over the
fajita mixture.
Serve
with
warm
flour
tortillas, guacamole, salsa and sour cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Put on apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dreamy creamy pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth and creamy.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip; mix well and pour into crust.
Refrigerate several hours. Top with other 1/2 of Cool Whip.

title: easy banana muffins
directions: Blend sugar and salad dressing.
Add mashed bananas and dry ingredients.
Stir lightly.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.
They will be very moist.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: crockpot vegetable soup
directions: Season stew beef and ground beef with salt and pepper while browning.
Place meat in crockpot and sprinkle with dry soup mix. Add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and sugar; mix well.
Add frozen vegetables and water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low heat 4 to 6 hours.
Add potatoes and cabbage; cook on low heat 1 to 2 more hours.

title: melanzane imbottite(stuffed eggplant)
directions: Wash eggplants, cut in half lengthwise and scoop out center, leaving 1/2-inch wall.
Cut center into pieces and set aside. Place small amount of olive oil in skillet and saute hamburg, parsley, onions, salt, pepper and mushrooms together.
Cook until hamburg browns.
Toss with fork.
Add tomato sauce and cook 15 minutes.
Add cut up pieces of eggplant and cook 15 minutes more, stirring.
Add rice.
Cook 5 minutes.
Grease outside of eggplant with olive oil.
Sprinkle inside with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle top with Romano cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Make
brine
using
ingredients listed.
Soak turkey 24 hours. Rinse
off
brine and dry with paper towels.
Oil bird lightly with
salad
oil.
Anchor neck skin.
Place turkey on rack in roaster,
breast side down.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 250° for 9 to 10 hours.	Do not cover.
When done, let turkey lay
on breast so juice runs into breast.
I use turkey breast.

title: fizzy soda pancakes(best pancakes ever)
directions: Mix well and pour onto hot griddle for pancakes or into your waffle iron for delicious waffles.

title: southern chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour with buttermilk and shortening.
Mix well.
Gradually add more flour until it forms a very firm dough.
Roll out on a floured surface to about 1/8 inch thick. Cut into 1 1/2 inch wide strips.
Bring the broth to a rolling boil.
Before dropping the strips of dough into the broth, break each strip into small pieces and press each piece with the fingers to flatten it.
Drop the dough strips into the broth. Reduce heat to medium and cover the pot.
Cook for about 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove lid and add milk. Continue cooking uncovered until broth thickens.
Stir in chicken and season with black pepper and butter.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Let set until it begins to congeal.
Mix sugar and cream cheese together until smooth.
Mix Jell-O in cream cheese mixture.
Whip Pet milk, which has been chilled, until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese and Jell-O mixture. Pour over graham cracker crust and let stand for several hours. You can put a small can of pineapple on top if you desire.
You may also sprinkle graham cracker on top.

title: sour cream cranberry coffee cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add sour cream, vanilla, flour and soda.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour half of the batter in greased tube pan.
Spread cranberry sauce and nutmeats over batter.
Pour rest of batter over cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together the eggs and milk.
Add flour and salt.
Beat with a fork until mix is uniform.
Now, add any extra flavorings.
Preheat muffin tin for 5 minutes.
Then brush each cup with melted butter.
Fill each cup 3/4 full with batter.
Keep muffin tin hot by working quickly.
Bake for 35 minutes, never opening oven until done.
Then prick each popover with fork to hold its shape.
Serve immediately.

title: spaghetti salad(pasta salad)
directions: Break spaghetti in 3 pieces.
Cook, then drain.
Mix the Ranch dressing and the Zesty Italian.
Mix with cucumbers, tomatoes, green peppers and purple onion.

title: applesauce crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix applesauce, brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon in a 9-inch square pan.
Heat for 15 minutes.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over applesauce mixture.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: In sauce pan, over medium heat, melt chocolate with salt and Eagle Brand.
Cook and stir until thick and fudgy (approximately 5 to 8 minutes); add water, cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat, add vanilla; let cool for 15 minutes. Chill 20 to 30 minutes, stir; folding in whipped cream.
Pour mixture into pie shell and chill three hours.
Garnish as desired.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/2 cup of pecans.
Chill.
Form ball and roll top in remaining nuts.
Decorate with maraschino cherries, if desired.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: molasses bread(1940)
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown, in loaf pan, 13 x 9-inch.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Dip biscuits in margarine and sugar.
Arrange in Bundt pan on edge.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: ricotta cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl, except flour and marinara sauce.
Form balls (meatball size) and roll in flour. Place on flat dish, cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight. Place balls in boiling, salted water for 5 to 7 minutes until they float on top.
Place balls in casserole dish and cover with marinara sauce and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain fruit well, add jello, marshmallows and walnuts.
Blend in Cool Whip and chill.

title: cheese ball with dry beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except optional ingredients. Cover and chill about 8 hours.
Form into a ball and roll in very finely shredded dried beef, parsley or chopped walnuts.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Press pretzels, 1 1/3 cup sugar and margarine into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Blend 1 cup sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Stir water and jello together until jello dissolves.
Stir in frozen strawberries until thickened and kind of cool.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: gelatin delight salad
directions: Put Jell-O, water and marshmallows in bowl.
Let stand until slighlty cooled.
Add salad dressing, cottage cheese, cream, celery, carrots and nuts.
Mix well and chill.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies into crumbs.
Mix ice cream and Cool Whip with cookies.
Freeze until set.
Serve frozen.
Makes one (9 x 13-inch) pan full.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together shortening, butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Blend well. Add chocolate chips and nuts and mix well.
Spray cookie sheets with Pam.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed beef flank
directions: Brush meat with melted oleo.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Spread on beef flank.
Roll up jelly roll fashion and tie with string.

title: texas beer chili
directions: Brown meat in large skillet until fat is cooked off.
Transfer to an 8-quart stockpot or crock-pot.
Saute onions and garlic in remaining pan drippings until tender.
Add meat and mix well.
Add chili powder, cumin, oregano, paprika, sugar and ground chili peppers to taste.
Add tomato sauce, canned tomatoes, bouillon and beer.
Mix well and simmer 2 hours.
Mix masa with enough hot water to make a light paste and add to chili 30 minutes before serving to thicken.

title: mrs. deweese's frosting
directions: Cook sugar, Karo syrup and water and let cook to soft ball stage.
Add egg whites which have been beaten stiff.
Add vanilla.

title: banana split
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs and melted butter and press in pan.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken and pork
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 20 minutes, uncovered.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Pour this sauce over the meat being prepared and cover it with foil.
Cook slowly, basting a few times, until meat is tender.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(If making more than one, mix one at a time.)

title: pennsylvania dutch cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage and carrots; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage mixture; toss well and refrigerate overnight.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate intrigue
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 3 eggs.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with milk and vanilla, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Turn 2/3 of batter into well-greased and floured pan.
Add to remaining 1/3 of batter, the 3/4 cup chocolate syrup and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda.
Mix well.
Spoon chocolate batter over white batter.
Do not mix!!
Bake in 350° oven in 10-inch tube pan for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: sausage cheese braid
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add sugar, salt, Italian seasoning, 1 egg, butter and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Perk in coffee pot using juice and cider in place of water and using spices in place of coffee.

title: fried lumpia
directions: Saute garlic and onion in hot oil.
Add ground beef; season with salt, Patis and pepper.
Cover and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add turnips and sweet potato; saute for 5 minutes.
Add green beans and bean sprouts; cook for 2 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Let Cool Whip soften.
Combine lemon juice and milk, then set aside.
Combine crumbs and margarine to form crust.
Pour the filling into the crust and spread evenly.
Arrange bananas.
Top with the following:
pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut, nuts and cherries.
Use a 13 x 9-inch dish and set overnight.

title: chicken beaudine
directions: Mix eggs and broth.
Pour over bread and celery and mix.
Add salt and onion.
Mix.
Add chicken.
Pour into greased pan and bake slowly (300°) until well done.
(Knife will come out clean.) Cut in squares and serve with gravy.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Mix gelatin with just enough pineapple to dissolve gelatin. Mix sugar and lemon juice and remaining pineapple juice and heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Pour gelatin mixture into hot mixture. Place in refrigerator to cool.
When cool fold in cottage cheese, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
(Strawberries can be used.)
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: hojun's drunk chicken
directions: In roasting pan, place chicken breasts.
Season to taste. Pour 2 to 3 cans of beer over chicken (depending on how thirsty the chicken is).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in Pyrex bowl or pan in oven.
Pour batter over melted oleo.
Pour can of sweetened
peaches or other fruit, juice and all, into pan after batter has been poured in.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse chicken in water, removing excess fat.
Dip chicken in bread crumbs until completely covered and place in 9x13 pan.
Bake 20 minutes uncovered.
Pour sauce over chicken and top with cheese.
Bake another 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Servings 4.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9x9 baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Pour pie filling into mixture.
Do not stir, just spoon around fairly evenly.
Bake at 325 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: jequillia's pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown the ground beef in skillet; drain it very well.
Place the buns on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread the Ragu pizza sauce on buns.
Add ground beef, pepperoni, cheese and onion.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the cheese is melted. Choice of topping is upon one's request.
Makes 10 to 12 single pizzas.

title: angel food crunch cake
directions: Cut cake in two lengthwise.
Chop candy bars into small pieces.
Set 1/4 cup of candy crumbs aside.
Mix rest of candy crumbs with Cool Whip and spread over bottom half of cake. Replace top of cake and spread the rest, like icing.
Dribble candy crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, poppy seed and sauce; then slice rolls in 1/2.
Spread mixture on both sides of rolls.
Then place ham and cheese on rolls and place top layer on.
Back in foil pan, wrap top with foil and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs and sugar and add melted butter.
Press into cheese cake pan about 1/2 way up the side.
Bake 10 minutes in 350 degree oven.
Beat cream cheese and 1 egg, 3/4 c. sugar, add other 3 eggs and vanilla (real).
Beat until well blended but no longer than necessary.
Over beating causes cake to split. (I found out after many splits.)
Bake for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with sour cream mixed with 1/2 c. sugar.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Cool and refrigerate.
Just before serving, top with 1 can cherry pie filling or sweetened strawberries.

title: angel rolls
directions: Mix well and fill muffin tin half full (grease tins).
Bake at 475° for about 10 minutes.
They are easy and quick to fix.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Mix well and chill Form small balls flatten with glass that has been dipped in white sugar.
Bake @ 350 for 10-12 minutes.

title: cream puff torte
directions: Heat water and butter to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour and then stir until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs thoroughly one at a time until smooth.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Beat pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
Let set in the refrigerator about 10 minutes.
Spread cool whip on top.
Drizzle Hershey's chocolate syrup on top.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: blueberry dessert(number served: 10 to 12 people; needed: 11 x 7-inch pan)
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cook to a golden brown, then let cool.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of this mixture for top garnish.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Put chicken in the bottom of a crock pot; then add the rest of the ingredients, except the spaghetti.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Cook spaghetti according to instructions on the package. Then serve the sauce and chicken breasts over spaghetti with parmesan cheese.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados.
Combine all ingredients into food processor or blender and blend well.
Serve with Pollo Flauta.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove seeds from peppers.
Boil the pepper halves in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients with the beef.
Stuff peppers with this mixture.
Bake, covered, for about 20 minutes. Top with sliced cheese, if desired, and bake 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: calico beans
directions: While browning meat and onions, mix the remaining ingredients. Add to browned meat.
Put mixture into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: easy to do beef stew
directions: Melt butter.
Put beef and potatoes in butter.
Boil carrots in beef broth for 10 minutes.
Spray baking dish with pan spray.
Pour meat, potatoes, carrots and broth into pan.
Add stewed tomatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy buckeye
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend in sugar and mix well.
Form into balls in chocolate mix.
Use toothpick for dipping.

title: crabmeat medley
directions: Saute onions and garlic over medium heat in skillet sprayed with vegetable spray.
Remove from skillet.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add flour; cook over medium heat for 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Gradually stir in wine; continue cooking and stirring until mixture is thickened.
Add onion and garlic mixture and basil to sauce, then add carrots, broccoli and crabmeat to sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Add cooked pasta; toss gently.
Serves 6.

title: health bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine boiling water, molasses, salt, oil, raisins, wheat germ, oats and bran; cool.
Add softened yeast.
Stir in whole wheat flour and 2 cups white flour. Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Punch down; divide in half.
Shape into loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: salad supreme
directions: Slice broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.
Place in ice water. Let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Heat olive oil, Salad Supreme and vinegar.
Pour hot mixture over cold vegetables and mushrooms.
Let stand overnight in icebox.
Will keep for one week.

title: tostado dip
directions: Layer in a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan in order given. Serve with any tortilla chips.

title: opal's buttermilk cheese pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.	Add eggs, vanilla and salt, beating well.
Add the buttermilk.	Pour into deep-dish unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 352°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter; add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Frost cake when completely cooled.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix.
Fry, then pour mushroom or tomato sauce over, heat and serve.
Can be as a loaf, also.

title: soy chicken
directions: Remove all skin from chicken.
Put soy sauce, brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of garlic powder and dry mustard in a baking pan.
Mix ingredients with a fork, then add chicken thighs.
Coat chicken well with soy mixture.
While baking, turn chicken every 20 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: hobo lamb stew
directions: Saute ground lamb in olive; pour off fat.
Put in Dutch oven. Add chickpeas.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onions in olive oil. Add to lamb stew; add tomato sauce.
Add garlic, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add green beans, yellow pepper and tomato.
Cook 45 minutes on medium-low.
Put in bowls.
Drizzle with olive oil. Serve with salad and crusty bread.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix everything until smooth and creamy.
Pour into casserole. Put over topping.

title: vegetarian swiss steak and gravy
directions: Freeze, thaw, squeeze and cut tofu into 1/4-inch slices. Marinate tofu for 20 minutes in soy sauce, cayenne, yeast flakes, lemon juice, sage and spike.
Dip marinated tofu in flour and brown well in 1/3 cup oil.
Turn once.

title: shortcut barbecued chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soup, honey, mustard and onion powder.
Arrange chicken, bone side up, on rack in broiler pan. Brush chicken with soup mixture.
Broil 6-inches from heat for 30 minutes or until no longer pink and juices run clear, turning once and brushing often with soup mixture during cooking.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken wings(easy)
directions: Cut wings and boil 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients in medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place wings in 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Pour sauce over wings and bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(unbaked)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop onto wax paper and cool. (Crunchy peanut butter can be used.)

title: breakfast egg cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 cup cheese in bottom of pan.
Break eggs on top (break yolks).
Spread ham or sausage and mushrooms over eggs.
Pour whipping cream over mixture. Sprinkle with salt and pepper (lightly).
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl that has a tight fitting lid.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add buttermilk and yeast, dissolved in warm water.
Mix with spoon until all flour is moistened.
Cover bowl.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Take out as much dough as needed.
Shape in a ball.
Roll on a floured cloth.
Cut as biscuits.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in 400° oven about 12 minutes or until brown.
Dough will keep several days.

title: angel flake biscuits(taste like yeast rolls)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and mix in buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients to yeast mixture.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Grease pan lightly.
May be refrigerated for future use.

title: devil dog surprise
directions: Cut devil dogs into halves lengthwise.
Arrange cream side up in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine milk and pudding mix in bowl. Beat until thick.
Spread over devil dogs.
Top with whipped topping and chopped candy.
Chill for 1 hour or longer, if desired.
Yields 16 servings.

title: broiled roast steak
directions: Dry steak in a paper towel.
Rub both sides with oil and place in a flameproof dish.
Set close under a very hot broiler. Rapidly brown both sides.
Season each side with salt and herbs and brush with soft butter.
Finish cooking in the oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once (125° on a meat thermometer for rosy rare; longer for well done).
Remove steak to a carving board.
Spoon fat out of the baking dish.
Pour in the wine or bouillon and boil over high heat on top of the stove, scraping up congulated juices.
When liquid is syrupy, remove from the heat, swish in final butter, pour over steak and serve.
It's nice to decorate serving dish with mashed potatoes but through a decorative cake flue.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together the gelatin, water and pie filling.
Chill until firm and well set.
Mix together the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until creamy, then pour the mixture over the firmly set gelatin mixture.
Chill until ready to serve, at least 2 hours.
Then cut into squares before serving.

title: hot spiced tea mix
directions: Combine in tightly covered jar.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, mix rice and soup.
Add broccoli. Top with Velveeta cheese slices.
Place in oven or microwave. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: pickled beans
directions: String and break green beans in pieces, about 1-inch long. Wash and cook until they are tender (about 1 1/4 hours).
Wash them again in cold water and pack in a crock-jar, alternating a layer of beans with a thin layer of salt.
When the jar is full, add enough water to fill all empty spaces.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese in microwave.
Add Vanilla.
Mix in cocoa.
Mix in nuts and powdered sugar quickly.
Spread into a 9 X 13 pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookie dessert
directions: Freeze the cookie dough until firm (about 1 hour). Cut one roll of cookie dough into 24 slices and lay them in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

Mix the softened cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and eggs together, then pour this mixture over the cookies in the pan. Cut the other roll of cookie dough into 24 slices and lay these on top of the mixture in the pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° until cookie mixture is set and brown.
It puffs up and flattens after it has cooled.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef until well done.
Add cooked carrots and onions, then add all vegetables and juice.
Cook for about 20 minutes.

title: deep dish peach cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: rolls(yeast: no kneading)
directions: Pour boiling water over butter or margarine, salt and sugar. Add cold water, egg, yeast and flour.
Cover and keep refrigerated for several hours (2 to 3).
Shape into rolls with flour dusted hands and place on greased pan.
Let rise 2 hours.
(Will take less time if kitchen is warm.)
Bake 15 minutes or until slightly brown at 350°.

title: russian rock cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Add flour and soda. Mix well. Add nutmeg, then chopped nuts. Mix well. Drop 1/2 tsp. batter onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes on 350 degrees. Makes 5-6 dozen cookies.

title: lemon bisque desserts
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, lemon juice, rind and honey.
Let congeal until nearly set.
Beat milk until stiff, then add jello and continue beating until well mixed.
Put half of wafer crumbs in bottom of a dish or pan larger than 8 x 8-inch.
Pour mixture on top of the crumbs, then cover with the rest of crumbs.
Put in icebox for an hour or longer.
May also use lime jello.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix raisins, soda and water; let stand overnight.
The next morning, add the brown sugar, flour and the salt; mix well. Lightly grease a 5 x 9-inch bread pan; pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and Ritz crackers. Place in greased casserole dish.
Pour butter over top.
Sprinkle crackers over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add bananas and nuts last.
Bake in 3 (10-inch) cake pans at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: almond jello
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in saucepan; heat and dissolve.
Add milk and extract.
Chill in pan until firm in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with mandarin orange slices or your favorite fresh or canned fruit.

title: society salad
directions: Make jello.
Once set, beat in last 5 ingredients.

title: mo's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add milk, melted butter and vanilla. Mix sugars and flour together.
Add egg mixture and stir.
Fold in nuts and pour in unbaked pie shell (9-inch deep dish).
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Mix together all ingredients and press in 15 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of the potatoes and onion; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers. Combine the soup and sour cream; pour over potato mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, brown pork chops on both sides.
Place chops on top of casserole.
Cover and return to the oven for 45 minutes or until chops are tender, uncovering during the last 15 minutes of baking.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place beef
in	large
Dutch oven.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Add onion,
sugar,
bay
leaf, garlic and peppercorns. Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered. Cut cabbage into 8 wedges.

title: four layer torte
directions: Beat cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip (or more); spread on cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk. Beat until thick.
Spread on cheese layer.
Top with more Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10.
May be frozen, if desired.

title: old-fashioned butter one pound cake
directions: Butter should be at room temperature; soft, but not melted.

title: beef jerky(6 servings)
directions: Slice beef across grain in 1/4-inch slices.
Place in a shallow dish.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 150°.
Lay beef strips on a rack set over an aluminum foil lined pan.
Place in oven; prop oven door open with a pencil.
Bake for 8 to 12 hours, or until meat is dry and chewy.
Perfect for snacking.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Generously grease bottom only of 13x9 pan. Remove 1/2 C. dry cake mix, reserve.
Beat remaining dry cake mix, butter, eggs and sour cream in large bowl on med. speed 2 min. Spread half of batter in pan.
Stir together reserved dry cake mix, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon, sprinkle over batter in pan. Carefully spread remaining batter evenly over pecan mixture.
Bake 30-33 min. or until deep golden brown.
Stir powdered sugar, milk and vanilla until thin enough to drizzle, stirring in additional milk, if necessary.
Poke top of warm cake several times with fork, spread glaze over top of cake.
Cool completely about 1 hour. Store covered.

title: pork chop spanish rice(one skillet meal)
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown in oil 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix salt and chili powder.
Sprinkle over chops.
Add rice, onion and chopped green pepper.
Pour tomatoes over.
Cover and cook over low heat 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add green pepper rings and cook 5 minutes longer or until rice and meat are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Add sour cream and onion soup mix to spinach.
Put in casserole.
Melt margarine and add crumbs and cheese to margarine.
Pour over top of spinach.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp aspic
directions: Grease mold with mayonnaise; set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: salad dressing for vegetable salad
directions: Mix all, adding vinegar last.
Salad of romaine lettuce, iceberg lettuce, purple onion, avocado and tomato.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into thin slices.
Combine butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over potatoes in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with crumbled bacon and bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: crunchy double chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and soda; set aside. In large bowl, beat together sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients mixing until thoroughly combined.
Add 2 cups of crushed cornflakes, chocolate and peanut butter morsels.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls into remaining cereal coating dough completely.
Place 2-inches apart on slightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack before storing in airtight container.
Yields 36 cookies; 1 cookie equals 140 calories.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Fold Cool Whip into cottage cheese, blending well.
Sprinkle the dry gelatin into the mixture and stir gently to combine.
Stir in mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar; stir in marshmallows.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine shortening, margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring to boil and heat until shortening and margarine melt.
Remove from heat and pour over flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk and eggs.
Pour into greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from oven and leave in pan.

title: old-fashioned chocolate icing
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk gradually; cook over medium heat in a thick-bottomed pot, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool and spread on cake.

title: classic crisco crust(10-inch double crust)
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender until all flour is blended in to form pea-size chunks. Sprinkle water 1 tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with fork until dough will form a ball.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each crust separately.
Press dough ball between hands to form a 5 to 6-inch "pancake".
Flour rolling surface and pin lightly.
Roll dough into circle.
Trim 1 inch larger than upside-down pie plate. Loosen dough carefully.
Fold in quarters.
Unfold and press into pie plate.
Trim edge even with pie plate.
Moisten pastry edge with water.
Add desired filling to unbaked pie shell.
Roll top crust same as bottom and place on top of filled pie.
Trim 1/2 inch beyond edge of pie plate.
Fold top edge under bottom crust and flute.
Cut slits in top crust or prick with fork.
Bake according to filling recipe.

title: best fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts in a large bowl.
Sift dry ingredients over fruit and mix well. Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla. Blend into fruit. Batter will be stiff. Grease and put waxed or parchment paper in angel food cake pan and a loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour at 275° and 1 hour at 250°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan. Store in refrigerator.
Can leave cake in pan until you use it, then wrap in a cloth and store in refrigerator. Slice thin. Once all the fruit and nuts are mixed, the cake is simple.

title: chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except milk.
The liquid pre-melted chocolate will make tiny chocolate chips.
I use a small rotary hand beater to mix together. Pour into one gallon ice cream freezer can.
Add milk to fill line on can.
Freeze according to instructions with your ice cream freezer.

title: french toast with peaches
directions: Drain peaches; reserve syrup.
Set aside.
In saucepan, heat sugar and butter on low heat until melted.
Add water; cook until thick and foamy.
Pour into a glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Place peaches on top; cover with slices of French bread, close together.
Blend eggs, milk and vanilla; pour over bread (I spoon it on to get it even).
Cover pan with Saran Wrap; refrigerate overnight.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.
In a casserole, combine vegetables, soup, sour cream and 1/2 the French fried onions.
After mixing ingredients, sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: jambalaya
directions: Put all ingredients in pot or oblong pan and mix well.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir after 1 hour. Do not cover.
If using magnalite, add 15 minutes to cooking time. Check at 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a medium bowl combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: ultimate cole slaw
directions: Combine desired amounts of cabbage and broccoli hearts with sunflower seeds, bacon bits and raisins.

title: texas crackers
directions: Whisk together the first five ingredients. Pour over crackers, stirring to coat. Place on baking sheets and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: walnut cake
directions: Blend together butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and blend.
Beat eggs separately and then add to mixture.
Add salt to flour, then add flour and milk alternately to mixture.
Next, add nuts and flavoring.
Beat until like whip cream.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour and 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crepes
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Cook in pan.
Fill crepes with fruit, vegetables, etc.
Warm prepared crepes in butter in chafing dish with toasted almond slivers.

title: mystery fruit cake
directions: Make cake as per box directions.
Cool and crumble in large bowl.
Add the fruit and nuts.
Prepare frosting mix as per box directions.
Mix with cake and nut mixture until damp and well blended.
Pack lightly in foil lined pans.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours until set.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: baked french onion soup with cheese toast
directions: Melt butter in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion and saute 15 minutes or until onions are tender and golden.
Add broth.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat waffles
directions: Put into large bowl:
whole wheat flour, white flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Mix in small bowl:
eggs or egg substitute, low-fat milk and melted oleo.
Combine the egg and milk mixture with the dry ingredients.
Pour 3/4 cup of batter into heated waffle iron.
Bake for approximately 2 1/2 minutes.

title: hot pickled okra
directions: Leave okra whole, without stemming, but pierce with a fork. Bring water. vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pack okra lengthwise into 6 sterilized hot pint jars.
To each jar add 1 jalapeno, 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill.
Pour boiling vinegar into each jar within 3/4 inch of jar top.
Process in water bath 5 minutes.
Seal jars. Let stand 3 to 4 weeks before serving.

title: hot spam sandwiches
directions: Grind Spam together with onion, mustard and sweet relish.
Mix and add tomato soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place on bun (around 2 tablespoons) with a strip of Velveeta cheese.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: dazzling strawberry 'n avocado salad(mother's recipe)
directions: In small bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cheese, milk, ginger and 3 tablespoons limeade concentrate until smooth.
Set aside.
In large bowl, toss avocado and strawberries with remaining limeade.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Cut together or use pastry cutter until pea size or smaller first 3 ingredients.
Beat last 3 ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook beans until almost done.
Pack in jars to 1/2-inch from top.
Put water,
salt and vinegar in pan (not aluminum). Mix well.
Pour over
beans
and
seal.
Store
in cool place. Makes 4 quarts.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add the scalded milk and cook until it starts to get thick.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Cool and put in a baked pie shell and top.

title: apple crumble pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and lemon peel. Sprinkle apple slices with lemon juice and add sugar mixture; toss and coat.
Fill an unbaked pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with mixture.

title: texas straw hats
directions: Brown ground beef with celery and onion in margarine in a large skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly.
Drain. Add tomato paste, catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, chili powder, thyme, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour. Serve over corn chips and top with cheese. Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat each addition.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
End with flour addition. Add lemon extract.
Blend in coconut by hand.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
