title: braised celery hearts
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil in medium saucepan.
Reduce heat after mixture comes to boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove bay leaf and cloves.
Drain.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Add water, just enough to cover veggies and cook until well done.
Add milk.
Mash half of the potatoes to get the creamy effect.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown
and drain
ground
beef.
Combine
ground
beef, tomato sauce, taco mix and
refried beans.
Put 2 cups crushed chips into casserole dish.
Spoon
in	meat mixture.
Cook for 20 minutes in 350° oven.	Add
lettuce,
cheese and corn chips as a topping. Cook 5 minutes longer in oven to melt cheese.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer the graham cracker crumbs, milk, chocolate chips, coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 2 hours before cutting into squares.
Makes 36.

title: one-pot meal
directions: Mix together in crock-pot and cook on low while you are at work.
Add any vegetables desired, even a can of mixed vegetables (cabbage, celery, broccoli, mushrooms, etc.).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen pistachio salad
directions: Blend pudding and sour cream.
Stir in coconut and pineapple. Pour into a loaf pan or muffin tin and freeze.
Serve on a bed of crisp lettuce.

title: vegetable paella
directions: In a flat bottomed pan, saute onions in oil over low heat until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, leeks, artichokes, peppers, asparagus and peas.
Add 1 cup stock.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Blend in garlic, parsley and remaining stock.
Season to taste. Add rice and cook over medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes, until rice is cooked and all liquid has evaporated.
Stir in saffron and let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: franklin pecan cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add beaten eggs.
Mix 3 cups flour, salt and baking powder together and add to batter.
Dice the fruit, chop nuts and mix with the other cup of flour. Add to batter with vanilla. Cook in greased and floured tube pan at 250° for 3 hours or until done.
Do not use mixer.

title: caramel apple cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place pie crust on baking sheet. Pour 1/2 can of apple pie filling into crust and spread evenly; set aside. With a mixer, beat together cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition. Pour filling over apple layer. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to directions.
Cool.
Combine pudding with cold milk.
Fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Put 1/3 cup coconut in mixture; pour into cooled crust.
Top with additional Cool Whip to cover.
Garnish with toasted coconut. Refrigerate.
Enjoy!

title: aladdin chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder, salt and sugar.
Sift together 3 times.
Add butter.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring until all flour is dampened.
Add chocolate and blend.
Then beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in a moderate 325° oven for 1 hour. Frost.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Mix peaches and 1 cup sugar.
Combine the 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt; add eggs and blend well.
Add milk and cook slowly until slightly thickened.
Let cool.
Add whipping cream, vanilla and sweetened peaches.
Pour into freezer container and freeze. Yield:
1 gallon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take dressing and put in bowl.
Melt margarine and put on top. Mix and set aside.
Cook chicken.
Cut up into bite size pieces. Mix soups and eggs together.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine all except Cheddar cheese.
Put in casserole and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash apples and remove core.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and add to center of apples.
Dot tops with margarine.
Place apples in a baking dish. Add water to baking dish so bottom of dish is covered with 1/4-inch of water.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes or until tender, but not mushy.
Baste apples with pan juices before serving.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles(fast and easy pickles, good too)
directions: Heat.
While
syrup
is
hot, pour over cucumbers.
Let set overnight covered.	The next day, drain syrup.
Reheat and pour again
over cucumbers, keeping lid on real tight to keep heat in.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: *Save 1/2 cup flour for nuts and raisins.

title: date sticks
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add 2 eggs and beat well.
Add nuts, dates and vanilla.
Spread on a well-greased and floured pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cut in sticks and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 36 sticks.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Preheat oven and make brownies according to package directions. Cool.
Prick with fork all over top and pour liqueur over top.
Set aside.
Break candy bars into small pieces into small bowl.
Set aside.
Prepare mousse filling according to directions.
Divide brownies into 3 equal sections.
Break 1/3 into bottom of trifle dish.
Spread 1/3 mousse.
Sprinkle 1/3 candy pieces.
Spread 1/3 Cool Whip.
Continue layers the same.
Finish with candy pieces. Garnish with shaved chocolate, if desired.

title: barbecue rumaki
directions: Wrap a piece of bacon on chestnut; secure with toothpicks. Cover with sauce.
Bake 1 hour.

title: barbecued pork
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook green peppers and onions until tender.
Stir i chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Add pork cubes, tomato paste, vinegar, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire and 1 cup water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring often, until meat falls apart with a fork.
With 2 forks, pull meat into shreds.
Serve on buns.
Makes about 7 cups, or enough for 14 sandwiches.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in microwave bowl on medium.
Stir to blend.
Pour in peanuts and stir.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: country casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and cook with onion and green pepper until tender.
Pour off fat.
Add beans, macaroni, tomato juice and salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 4 cups.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of sugar to sour cream and stir.
Drizzle over fruit and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Stir and serve.

title: dream delight
directions: Mix the top 3 ingredients together.
Cut the cookies in half. Keep mix in refrigerator until ready to use.
Put 1 teaspoon of mix between the cookies.
Enjoy yourself.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken with mayonnaise, onion, rice, soup, broth, salt and pepper.
Place in a baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers fine. Sprinkle evenly over chicken mixture.
Pour melted butter over the crackers.
Cook in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw vegetables and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased square baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick melted butter or Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: eggless chocolate pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa. Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Let it come to a boil about 10 minutes or until it thickens.
Add vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni; drain. Mix remaining ingredients. Add to macaroni. Toss gently to mix. Cover and chill thoroughly. Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and shortening.
Cool to room temperature.
Add orange peel and juice; stir in egg.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan.
Grease and flour pan or line with paper.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Chop chicken, then layer the broccoli in a casserole dish. Blend cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle the cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Put butter, water and cocoa in pot; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture. In a bowl, mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to first mixture; mix well with electric mixer.
Bake in greased, floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 or 30 minutes at 400°.
Frost in pan as soon as removed from oven.

title: michael's night to cook
directions: Make a decision on what to eat.
Pick up phone and place orders.
Pick up food.
Extra point with wife-clean up kitchen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs; add syrup, oleo and milk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350°.

title: apple nut ring
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip biscuit in butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Peel and thinly slice 3 Granny Smith apples.
Line edges and seams between biscuits with apples.
Sprinkle with 1/4 to 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade shake and bake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first six ingredients in a plastic bag.
Dip chicken in milk, shake off excess.
Add chicken to bag and shake to coat evenly.
Place chicken on greased, foil lined baking pan.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes until tender and coating is crisp.

title: crustini
directions: Cook ground beef until all meat is lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and pepper.
Let cook for 10 minutes.
In a frying pan, put a little olive oil and add anchovies.
Mash anchovies with fork as they soften, until they are all mashed.
Add anchovy mixture to ground beef and tomato sauce.
Let cook for 10 minutes, slowly, until tomato sauce gets taste of anchovies.
Toast slices of French or narrow Italian bread.
Spread with tomato and anchovy mixture.

title: scallops and rice au gratin(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in small amount of water in saucepan.
Heat until very thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and scallops.
Layer casserole dish with rice, scallop mixture and cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fried rice
directions: Rinse peas and carrots in cold water.
Heat 1 tablespoon cooking oil in pan.
Add peas, carrots and ginger.
Cook approximately 2 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon cooking oil in pan.
Add onions.
Stir and cook for 1 minute.
Add beaten eggs and scramble.
Add rice and stir until hot (about 5 minutes).
Add peas and carrots and mix well.
Add chopped pork, ham or shrimp.
Serve hot.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine ingredients; sprinkle heavily with the Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients except butter and set aside.
Make pastry.
Roll half the pastry and line a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill shell with berry mixture.
Dot with butter, cut into small pieces.
Roll out remaining pastry, moisten edges of lower crust, lay top crust on and seal.
Prick small holes all over crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in preheated 425° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
If crust browns too quickly, cover loosely with foil.

title: deviled cheese spread(for fish)
directions: Mix shredded Cheddar cheese with chili sauce, mustard and horseradish.
Spread on broiled fish.
Then broil 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese melts.
It's worth a try!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Remove from stove and add sour cream and soup.
In a casserole dish, layer squash, cheese and crumbled crackers.
Repeat until gone.
Place in oven at 350° and cook until bubbly.

title: crab cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use as a spread for crackers. Triscuits are a good choice.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate peanut supreme
directions: In a bowl, combine peanut butter and butter.
Stir in cracker crumbs and sugar and mix well.
Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Prepare pudding with milk according to package.
I use less milk to make it more solid.
Spoon over crust.
Spread with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or until set.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Heat small amount of oil in large skillet.
Fry chicken until brown.
Drain and place chicken in a baking dish.
In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until chicken is done.
Baste occasionally.

title: fajitas(low-fat)
directions: Separate flour tortillas.
Place in layers of aluminum foil. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Place all ingredients into tortilla with cheese.
Wrap.
Microwave for a few seconds.
Serve with salsa and guacamole.

title: elinor curham's mexican tomato relish
directions: Prepare home canning jars and lids according to manufacturer's directions.
Combine all ingredients in a large sauce pot.
Bring it to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until mixture thickens.
Carefully ladle into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in a boiling water bath canner.
Yields 6 pints.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Pour into a greased casserole dish and mix 1 "Jiffy" cornbread mix.
Drop on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cookies
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Beat until thickened and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: "chocolate dot pudding"
directions: Cook chocolate squares, sugar and water in double boiler until chocolate melts.
Add egg yolks, which have been beaten lightly, and cook a few minutes longer; let cool.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold in the whipped cream to the beaten egg whites.
Add this mixture to the cooled chocolate mixture.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and sugared Bundt pan. Grease well with oleo and shake sugar like you would when you flour a pan; it will stick on.
Sprinkle mixture of cinnamon and sugar on top of batter, then pour remaining batter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool 15 minutes or so before removing from pan.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add liquid mixture to flour mixture.
Mix until moist. Separate into 4 or 5 balls; freeze.
Thaw when needed.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Sprinkle inside pepper with salt.
Brown meat and onion.
Add corn, tomato, Worcestershire and salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Stuff peppers and stand in bowl. Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt together caramels and milk.
Set aside.
Prepare cake batter and pour 1/2 in baking pan.
Bake 14 minutes at 350°.
Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Add the other 1/2 of batter and bake at 350° until cake is done.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows; let melt in water.
Add cold water, pineapple and nuts.
Must let jell completely.

title: easy pickled peaches
directions: Mix peach syrup, brown sugar, and spices in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Add peaches and cool.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, serve cold.
Yields 1 quart.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together the beans, taco seasoning and ground beef. Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with the sour cream and cheese. Bake until bubbly.

title: lazy pierogi
directions: Simmer for one hour; do not let mixture get brown.
Add more butter if necessary.
Cook 1 package of twist noodles; drain.
Mix with sauerkraut mixture and add 1/2 stick of butter.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: cocoa pebbles s'mores bars
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil. Grease bottom and sides of foil-lined pan. Place graham crackers on bottom of pan, cutting crackers to fit.

title: manicotti
directions: Beat ingredients with beater until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls into 6-inch round frying pan rubbed with oil.
Turn when done on one side (few seconds).
Cook other side (few seconds also).

title: butter rum pound cake
directions: Generously grease and flour a Bundt cake pan. Beat dry cake mix, dry pudding mix and remaining ingredients in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed, 30 seconds, then medium speed 2 minutes. Pour into pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool completely, then dust with powdered sugar.

title: no cook white icing
directions: With mixer, beat slowly until ingredients are mixed, then beat on high speed until all sugar crystals are melted and fluffy. Spread on cool cake.

title: dan's favorite saucy steak skillet
directions: Cut
steak
into
bite-size
pieces
and coat in flour. Brown in
oil
in 10-inch skillet with onion about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Open cans of potatoes and pour liquid into measuring cup, adding water
to equal 1 1/2 cups.
To the potato liquid add
ketchup,
Worcestershire sauce, beef bouillon, salt, marjoram
leaves and pepper.
Mix and pour on beef and onion.
Add green
pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and
simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Cut whole potatoes in half and add them
and
green beans
to
skillet.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with bread; rather spicy dish.
Serves 4.

title: mexicorn lasagne
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large skillet. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan, oregano and garlic salt.
Mix well.

Arrange 6 tortillas on bottom and sides of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, overlapping as necessary. Top with half meat mixture. Bake in preheated 375° oven about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Remove from oven and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bobbi's dressing for turkey
directions: Saute onions and celery in sausage grease. Drain grease. Process sausage to fine texture.
Pour turkey juice into stuffing. Add 3 eggs and stir.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil using a 2-quart saucepan. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
No baking involved.

title: cereal candy
directions: Stir together in bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Boil to soft ball stage the cream, sugar and syrup and pour over the first mixture.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with strawberries, blueberries, bananas, grapes and all types of melons.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
(This should take about 2 months.)
Flour pieces; add salt and pepper to taste and enough water to make brown gravy.
Cook over a large fire (465°) for 4 weeks.
This recipe serves approximately 3,812 people.
If more are expected, add the rabbits, however, only if necessary, because most people don't like to find hares in their stew.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook cream and sugar together over medium heat.
Cook 8 minutes after it reaches a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Beat until it begins to form.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been slightly buttered.
Cut into squares.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix cornbread and chopped vegetables well.
Mix dressing, mayo and mustard well.
Toss into cornbread mixture.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together and blend well.
Then add nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes and enjoy.

title: hamburger supper
directions: Brown hamburger and season to taste; drain off excess fat.
Add mixed vegetables and soup; mix well.
Pour into ungreased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Remove pan from oven and place raw biscuits, spaced apart on top of meat mixture.
Return to oven at 400° for 10 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix coloring and cocoa together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add salt to buttermilk and add alternately with flour.
Add vanilla and soda.
Beat 2 or 3 minutes until well blended.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans, that have been greased and floured, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces, place in top of double boiler and melt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Mix all ingredients except for pork.
Pour into shallow container and add tenderloin, turning to coat.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Remove pork from marinade.
Grill for 35 minutes or until done or bake in oven at 350°.
To serve, slice thinly and arrange on platter.
Serve with hoisin and sweet and sour sauces.

title: pizza-size chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: health cake with zucchini
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Beat next four to blend. Stir in squash.
Gradually stir in flour mixture, keeping smooth. Stir in nuts.
Pour into oiled and floured 12 cup tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: light taco pie
directions: If using canned biscuits, press into a pan to form crust. Combine ground turkey and onion.
Lightly brown.
Add water, tomato paste and taco seasoning; cook for 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Layer meat mixture with cheese, ending with cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil 10 pint jars for 15 minutes.
Leave in hot water until ready to use.
Wash okra.
Leave short stems.
Pack in hot jars. Put one pepper and one clove of garlic in each jar. Add 1 teaspoon dill weed.
Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over okra and seal.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Blot ham slices so cheese will stick.
Peel onions and just use centers.
Spread layer of cheese on ham.
Place onion in and roll up. Chill and slice.

title: zucchini and eggplant casserole
directions: Trim ends of zucchini; do not peel.
Cut into 3/8-inch cubes. This should result in about 4 cups.
Trim ends of eggplants; do not peel.
Cut into 3/8-inch cubes.
This should result in about 4 cups.

title: nisu(finnish coffee cake)
directions: Mix sugar, butter, ground cardamon and salt together.
Add hot milk.
Mix and let mixture cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water.
Add dissolved yeast and eggs in cooled mixture.
Add flour gradually, working in well with a spoon.
Then knead with hands until firm and smooth.
Cover with a towel and let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 2 hours).

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken covered at 425° for 15 minutes; drain.
Mix other ingredients and heat them on stove.
Pour over chicken and bake 5 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in rectangular pan (13 x 9-inch).
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken. Place chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Turn; bake until done, about 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mulled spiced cider punch
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Refrigerate.
Make 32 balls from sherbet; place in freezer on cookie sheet.
Strain cider mixture when ready to serve; reheat. Add orange slices.
Serve over sherbet in punch cups or clear glasses.

title: holiday cranberry mold
directions: Add boiling water to jello; stir until dissolved and cool to room temperature.
Mix in jellied cranberry sauce and sour cream until mixture is smooth.
I use a food processor, but you can use a mixer on low speed or a blender in small batches.
Pour into mold or pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray or just into a bowl to chill and set.
Unmold onto plate before serving or serve from bowl.
Garnish with green grapes and pineapple chunks, if desired.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream oil, butter, salt and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Press down with a glass dipped into sugar.
Bake about 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter; add cream cheese (chop up for easier melting). Add mushroom liquid, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and stir. Add beans and mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour in greased casserole.
Sprinkle onions on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: italian chickpea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Serve with pita bread, cut in quarters.
Serves 4.

title: aunt eileen's german potato soup
directions: Place potatoes and onions into large pot, adding just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Do not drain.
Hand mash half of the potato mixture in the pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
While soup is simmering, cook sausage until crisp.
Drain well and add to soup.
Add half and half and fresh chopped parsley.

title: easter eggs
directions: Soften cream
cheese
and
butter.
Mix
cream	cheese, butter, sugar, peanut
butter and vanilla in large bowl. Chill for 2 hours,
then
shape
and chill overnight.
Next day melt chocolate morsels
and
paraffin
wax in slow cooker or double boiler for best results.
Dip eggs in chocolate.

title: banana split pie
directions: Spread bananas in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle pineapple over bananas.
Mix pudding and milk until thick and spread over pineapple.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: fried shrimp or onion ring batter
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Dredge shrimp or onion rings in flour mixture, then dip in buttermilk and then back into flour mixture. Shake off excess and fry in 350° hot oil until golden brown.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in a bowl and beat with eggbeater until smooth.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Bake on griddle or frypan. When a drop of water dances on griddle it is hot enough for your batter.
Place enough batter on griddle for your desired size of pancake.

title: cherry bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and beat until blended.
Stir in cherries, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Remove 1 cup dry cake mix and set aside.
Place remainder of cake mix in bowl; add melted oleo and 1 beaten egg.
Beat together with fork until all cake mix is absorbed.
Press into greased and floured baking pan (9 x 13-inches).

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar and stir well. Add flavorings, vinegar and melted butter. Makes 12 pies with 1/4 cup to each pie. We like Stilwell tart shells, some like Bama best. This will also make a regular pie. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: kentucky bourbon balls
directions: Put nuts through blender and add to bourbon. Soak for 2 hours. Mix sugar, milk, butter, bourbon and nuts.
Form into balls. Melt chocolate and paraffin and dip balls into mixture.
Put on wax paper.
Yield 5 pounds.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Empty Cool Whip into a bowl. Pour pudding mix over this and mix well. Add pineapple and blend, then fold in marshmallows and stir until all are blended. Add nuts. Chill or freeze. Cherries may be used to garnish.

title: reuben roll-ups
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard and caraway seeds. Add corned beef, cheese and sauerkraut. Toss and blend well. Unroll dough; cut in half and roll out. Spoon 1/2

of filling into each dough and roll long ways in jelly roll style. Arrange rolls, seam side down. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown. Let stand for 10 minutes. Cut into 1-inch slices. Serve with Thousand Island dressing.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil in a microwave-safe container that is at least 2-quarts deep. After it is boiling, cook on High 2 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.
Place corn in paper bag.
Pour mixture over corn.
Roll shut and shake.
Put in microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake.
Put in microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes more; remove and shake.
Allow to cool and enjoy.

title: orange kiss-me coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup orange juice concentrate with remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend at lowest speed of mixer 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Drizzle remaining orange juice concentrate over warm cake; sprinkle with topping.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well and spread in an ungreased 13 x 9 baking dish.

title: martian cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36 to 48 cookies.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter into the bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over the melted butter.
Sprinkle nuts over the crumbs evenly.
Scatter the chocolate chips over the nuts. Sprinkle the coconut over the chips.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool in the pan 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen 1 1/2 x 3-inch bars.

title: applesauce bran bread
directions: In small bowl, mix together applesauce and cereal.
In large bowl, mix together margarine, cinnamon, cloves and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix dry ingredients alternately into batter with applesauce-bran mixture.
Add raisins and walnuts, if wanted. Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: ritzy pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Place pineapple in baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of flour and sugar.
Pour reserved juice over top. Sprinkle with cheese and cracker crumbs. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ham.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: rotel
directions: Simmer or cook on low for 1 hour in open kettle.
Put in pint jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: Choose onions that are uniform in size.
Cook in boiling, salted water for about 25 to 30 minutes or until tender, but not soft.
Drain and cool.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet and saute onion and bell pepper. (I saute mine with the sausage.)
Drain grease off and mix with soups and rice.
Bake in a covered casserole at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover for last 10 minutes to brown.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs.
Mix cream of tartar and soda.
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
This is rather soft dough.
Roll in white sugar. Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 60 cookies.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix sour cream, oil, pudding, cake mix, and eggs well.	Pour 1/2 of batter into 11 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of chocolate chips and nuts over this.
Pour rest of batter and then rest of nuts. (Two layers of each.)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle equal amounts of remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: beef marsala
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil in a large stew pot until slightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients, beginning with liquids.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
If needed, add more liquid.
Thicken at end of cooking time, if necessary, or desired, with cornstarch and a small amount of the hot liquid.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: rhubarb jam with jello
directions: I make many jams and jellies and do not like to use a lot of sugar.

I also use wild berries, sometimes some that are unusual enough that there are no recipes, or it is hard to collect a lot. For those reasons, I have developed methods of making jellies without the commerical pectins that require exact amounts of berries and sugar.
With these directions I can also invent exciting new kinds of jams such as Blueberry-Banana and Cran-Raspberry (two of my favorites).
Some fruits do not require pectin.
Some require only a little.
Here are some ways to find out how much pectin is already in your fruit:

title: homemade chocolate pudding
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, salt. Gradually add milk. Bring to rolling boil over medium heat; boil and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla. Spoon into individual serving dishes. Chill until ready to serve.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots. Layer carrots, onion (sliced) and bell pepper rings in large casserole dish. Heat soup, sugar, oil, vinegar and Worcestershire until sugar dissolves. Pour over carrots-onion and pepper. Serve warm or cold.

title: dreamsicle punch
directions: Place vanilla ice cream and frozen orange juice concentrate in punch bowl.
Add pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Stir and serve.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in order and mix thoroughly.
Bake in regular layer cake pans which have been buttered, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: white bean, kale and roasted vegetable soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Spray rimmed baking sheet with oil spray. Arrange carrots, tomatoes, onion, squash and garlic on baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Toss to coat. Bake until vegetables are brown and tender, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.

title: polly's cheese pudding
directions: Layer casserole dish with the ingredients.
Top casserole with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and meat in butter.
Add other ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple, oranges and cherries.
Put in a bowl with walnuts and marshmallows.
Mix Dream Whip by directions and pour over fruit mix.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: brunswick stew(makes 75 quarts)
directions: My father-in-law made this in a big black pot outside over a fire.
We would split it between 4 families and freeze it.
Their church also made it as a fund raiser.
It is great on a cold rainy day with hot rolls or cornbread.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Combine and place in a pretty glass bowl and chill for several hours.
Delicious and delightful to look at as well.

title: pistachio dream salad
directions: Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip last.

title: scalloped ground beef and potatoes
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper in skillet for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently; drain. Arrange 1/3 of the potato slices in 2-quart baking dish.
Layer ground beef mixture and remaining potato slices 1/2 at a time in dish.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Pour over layers. Dot with margarine.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and margarine together.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place in buttered dish.

title: egg noodles
directions: Make a well in center of flour.
Add egg yolks, egg and salt; mix thoroughly.
Mix in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough is stiff but easy to roll.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll dough, one part at a time, in a very thin rectangle on a well floured board.
Loosely fold rectangle and place on a cookie sheet.
Dry dough in 350° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
Fold lengthwise and cut into very narrow strips.
Boil in chicken, turkey or beef broth for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with celery.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and water and spread over chicken.
Layer with crackers; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl.
(Add others, i.e. ham, broccoli, mushrooms), if desired. Put into the shell. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, apples, and sugar.
Set aside. Dissolve Jello in hot water and add pineapple juice.
Stir into cranberry mixture.
Add grapes, nuts and crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.

title: old time meat loaf
directions: Mix ground meat and oatmeal thoroughly.
Add the can of tomato sauce and onion.
Last add the egg.
Mix well.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, cornflakes and eggs.
In saucepan, mix jelly, barbecue sauce and lemon juice.
Heat until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Form beef mixture into balls and put in crock-pot.
Add cooked sauce mixture.
Cook on high until done.

title: ore-ida hash browns
directions: Melt margarine and mix with soup.
Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and mix again.
Bake uncovered in a 9x13 pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead and frozen before baked.

title: watermelon cake
directions: Sprinkle flour over cake mix.
Add gelatin, oil and melon. Mix thoroughly with electric mixer, adding one egg at a time. Bake in 2 greased 8-inch pans at 325°.
Ice when cool.

title: crabmeat-shrimp pasta salad
directions: Boil, peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Blend.
Combine mayonnaise, salad dressing, lemon juice and seasonings.
Add to macaroni mixture.
Stir in crabmeat and shrimp.
Chill.
Yields 7 servings.

title: potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut them in slices crosswise, about 1/4-inch apart, cutting within 1/4 or 1/2 of the bottom so that the potato remains whole. Place potatoes in melted butter pan. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle tops with more melted butter. Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Add more melted butter.
Cook for another 20 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook
and
cool
macaroni.
Mix first five ingredients. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble bread.
Melt butter and mix with bread;
sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread - made easy
directions: Cut refrigerator biscuits into 4 pieces.
Put 1/2 c. of the sugar and 3/4 tsp. of the cinnamon into a plastic bag.
Shake a few of the biscuit pieces at a time in the bag.
Put coated pieces of biscuits into a bundt cake pan.
Melt 1 cube of margarine in a sauce pan.
Add remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Pour
milk over stuffing cubes; mix in remaining ingredients. Press
evenly into loaf dish, 9 x 5 x 3-inches, cover loosely
and microwave
on High (100%) 10 minutes.
Turn loaf dish one
half turn.
Microwave until meat is set in center, 5 to 6 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in sugar, flour and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in nuts and chocolate morsels.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: flavored iced coffee
directions: Using your favorite gourmet coffee, double the amount of grounds you would use for normal drinking and brew.
When coffee is brewed, pour into a gallon container and fill up the rest of the way with milk (2% if you are watching fat grams).
Sweeten to taste.
Serve cold.

title: hong kong pork chops
directions: Salt chops and brown.
Cover with onion slices.
Mix soy sauce, sherry, lemon juice, mushrooms with juice, ginger and garlic powder and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add green pepper, water chestnuts (drained) and sliced lemon and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: glazed beets with crumbled blue cheese
directions: Scrub beets, do not peel.
Cut off tops.
Cover with water. Boil about 40 minutes or until fork tender; drain.
Run cold water over beets to cool; skin and slice.
Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch and cinnamon in small saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook and stir until mixture is clear and bubbling.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Pour over sliced beets and toss to coat well. Just before serving, sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: spam skillet dish
directions: Add all ingredients to skillet.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring some to prevent sticking.
Add small amounts of water as needed to prevent burning.

title: turkey layered casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Layer cooked rice, turkey, cooked broccoli, cheese slices, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Stir together soup, mayonnaise and chicken broth.
Pour over layers in dish.
Top with onions.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken burgers
directions: Finely grind chicken breasts in food processor.
Stir in 1 cup bread crumbs, cream, parsley, onions, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Shape into patties.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Dredge in bread crumbs.
Heat oil and butter in skillet and cook burgers until done.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix corn,
sugar
and
melted butter in 2 quart greased casserole.
Add Jiffy mix;
stir thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken broccoli oriental
directions: Cook chicken in skillet until browned.
Add onions and pepper; cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce, heat to boiling, reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in cookie sheet.
Spread graham crackers to form crust.
In a bowl, mix chocolate bits, nuts and coconut. Pour into cookie sheet and spread out evenly.
Pour 1 can of milk over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Cut potatoes with or without peeling lengthwise into wedges. Brush lightly with oil.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and oregano. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: heavenly cherry angel food trifle
directions: Place cake cubes in large bowl. In medium bowl, combine powdered sugar and cream cheese. Beat until well blended. Fold Cool Whip into cheese mixture, then stir with pecans into cake cubes. Mix well. Spoon cake mixture into a pretty glass of crystal bowl. Spread cherry pie filling over top or layer: 1/2 cake mixture, 1/2 pie filling, 1/2 cake mixture, 1/2 pie filling. Garnish with additional Cool Whip.

title: overnighter fresh lemonade
directions: You will need 2 empty gallon milk or water containers (cleaned).

title: arlene's pull apart cake
directions: Mix into a batter.
Make a paper funnel.
Pour into skillet of hot oil (not too much oil) in a swirling design.
Let fry until lightly browned.
Turn (turn only once to avoid getting soggy with grease).
When done and still hot, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: Place thawed turkey in roasting bag and bake at 350° about 4 to 6 hours.
The last hour of cooking, stuff with the following: Mix seasoned and cornbread dressings together with chicken broth, 2 cups chopped (finely) celery and 2 cups of chopped onions.
If more broth is needed, take from turkey bag.
Place prepared dressing around turkey and finish baking.
Turkey can be served whole on platter with dressing placed around it or you can debone turkey before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender, drain. Saute onions in 5 Tbsp. oleo until tender.
Add soup and mix well. Add cheese, stir until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in drained cabbage, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in ungreased 2 qt. baking dish.
In skillet, melt 1 Tbsp. oleo, stir in crumbs until lightly browned.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered 350° for 20-30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: On a round pizza tray (medium size), smooth out sour cream. Add salsa on top of sour cream.
Do not mix.
On top, grate Cheddar cheese, then Monterey Jack, then Cheddar or vice versa. Sprinkle scallions on top of cheese (as much as you prefer) and top with olives and tomatoes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and make into
1-inch
balls.
Freeze
on
a cookie sheet and then drop into	plastic bag.
Take out as needed and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: baked cushaw
directions: Wash outside of cushaw; remove all seeds. Do not peel. Cut cushaw into 3-inch pieces.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar on top and cover with the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: cordon bleus(appetizer)
directions: Roll ham and cheese slices together, cheese on the inside. Fasten with toothpicks.
Dip each roll in milk; roll in flour and dip in beaten eggs.
Roll in breadcrumbs.
Fry in margarine until browned, turning frequently.
Cut each roll into four serving pieces.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Steam onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Cook ground beef and drain fat.
Add corn, onion, green pepper, celery, rosemary, oregano, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Combine tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Pour half the sauce mixture over beef mixture and simmer 5 minutes.

title: low cholesterol golden cornbread
directions: Sift together the flour, meal, salt, baking powder and soda. Add egg substitute, milk and margarine, stirring only until mixed. Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400° or until brown.
One serving equals 0 mg cholesterol.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate spaghetti and dressing overnight.
Before serving, add the pepper, onion and tomatoes.

title: banana oatmeal pancakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oats, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In a smaller bowl, mash the banana.
Add egg whites, buttermilk, oil and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Add to dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Spoon batter onto griddle.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Drain
the whole kernel corn.
Melt butter and mix with sour cream.
Beat the eggs, then add all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put in baking dish, then mix together Ritz crackers, crushed, and margarine, softened.
Spread on top and bake until it bubbles or just browns a little, about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Use a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Grind together green onions, peppers, celery and parsley.
Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart.
Great to eat with boiled shrimp.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Stir over low heat until blended the tomato soup and cream cheese.
Mix gelatin and juice.
When dissolved, add to soup mix and cool.
Add the Miracle Whip, onion, celery and green pepper. Then add the two small cans of tiny shrimp.
Mix well and chill for several hours.

title: parslied potatoes
directions: Peel a strip of skin from around the middle of each potato; place potatoes in cold water. Set aside. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat; add oil. Saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes or until tender. Add broth and 3/4 cup parsley; mix well. Bring to a boil. Place potatoes in a single layer in skillet. Return to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove potatoes with a slotted spoon to serving bowl. Add pepper to skillet; stir. Pour sauce over potatoes. Sprinkle with remaining parsley.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients (save 1/4 c. pecans).
Mix well. Pour into shallow serving dish.
Top with pecans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: szekely gulyas
directions: Rehydrate minced onion in 1/3 cup water for 10 minutes; set aside.
In a large heavy saucepot, heat bacon fat.
Add pork; brown on all sides, a few pieces at a time; remove and set aside. To drippings left in saucepot, add sauerkraut and rehydrated onion; saute until golden, about 5 minutes.
Return pork to saucepot.
Stir in 1 cup water, wine, paprika, caraway, salt, tarragon, black pepper and bouillon cube.
Bring to the boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until pork is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat until hot.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Serve with cooked noodles, if desired. Yields 6 to 8 portions.

title: slush
directions: Steep first 3 ingredients 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: nonnie's shortnin' bread
directions: Soften butter at room temperature and cream with sugar.
Add 2 cups of flour, then add 1/2 cup extra flour, if needed, while kneading with hands.
(Only add flour until dough cracks, not crumbles.)
Place on cookie sheet and press and smooth until it covers the pan.
Sprinkle with sugar; prick all over with fork. Bake in slow oven at 275° for almost an hour (if 1/2-inch thick). Should be light golden brown when finished.
Cut into squares while still hot, then let cool on pan.
Great, easy dessert.
Kids will love it!

title: perked punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a coffeepot and perk.
Serve warm.

title: candy cookie pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough in well-greased pizza pan at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
No longer!
You want the crust chewy, not too done. Remove from oven and spread with peanut butter.
Top and decorate with whatever candy, raisins or nuts you choose.
Suggestions: Holiday-colored M & M's, chocolate chips, Heath (candy bar) bits, Reese's pieces and candy corn.
Decorate as you wish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the sugar and water to soft ball stage.
Add margarine, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered pans.
Let cool, then cut.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well with a fork. Add shortening; mix until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat together water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures; mix until moist.
Divide dough in equal flat round patties ready for rolling.
Wrap in plastic.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook celery, onion, bell pepper and carrot in butter.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Stir in rice, water and broth.
Heat to boiling point.
Stir in half and half; almonds for garnish.
Do not boil this soup.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend first two ingredients well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Place teaspoonful (rounded) on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with floured fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: bean curd with oyster sauce
directions: Mix together the oyster sauce, 3 of the scallions, the soy sauces, sugar, chicken stock and cornstarch and set aside.
Heat the oil in a skillet.
When very hot, add the tofu and fry gently until light brown.
Add the sauce and turn down the heat.
Stir to coat.
Serve when the sauce thickens, topped with remaining scallions.
Serve with brown rice and vegetable or salad.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni according to package instructions. Add next four ingredients while still warm.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: veggie cheddar chowder
directions: Combine vegetables with 2 cups water. Bring to a boil, then simmer 10 minutes. Do not drain.
Make a white sauce with butter, flour and milk. Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Add vegetables and water.
Heat through.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and baking soda.
Add oil, eggs and pineapple; mix thoroughly.
Bake on greased and floured sheet pan (18 x 21 x 1-inch) at 350° until brown (20 to 25 minutes).
Use Barb's Pineapple Frosting.

title: ashley effron's favorite broccoli with cheese
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Melt Velveeta cheese or make white sauce and add Velveeta to sauce.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Immediately before serving, pour cheese sauce over broccoli.

title: grandma gay's barbecue sauce
directions: So here it is, as you will want to again make it and remake it, for one seldom grows tired of it.

title: cold lemon cake
directions: Mix pudding with water.
Mix sugar with egg yolks.
Add sugar and egg yolks to pudding and water.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and lemon juice. Let cool well.
Fold whipped cream into pudding mixture.
Use as filling and icing.
Place cake in refrigerator to get cold and pudding to jell.
Serve cold.

title: raisin cake
directions: Combine raisins, brown sugar, shortening and butter, cinnamon and boiling water and bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Stir in soda sifted with flour.
Stir in enough flour to make cake batter.
Pour into two 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in chicken broth and onions.
Saute sausage. Add to potatoes and broth.
Add whole kernel corn.
Add whipping cream.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: confetti cole slaw
directions: Toss vegetables together in a salad bowl.
In a small mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, sugar, salt and seasoned pepper. Pour over vegetables and toss lightly until thoroughly mixed.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix egg, sugar and shortening in a large bowl.
Add baking soda to applesauce, then add to mixture in bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add rice.
Add beef consomme and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses and 1/2 cup onions.
Chill.
Shape into ball. Roll in remaining onions.

title: cinnamon-frosted zucchini bars
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
In a large bowl, beat margarine with electric mixer on medium speed 30 seconds.
Add two sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Stir in zucchini, coconut and nuts.
Spread evenly in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.

title: eggs portugal
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread cubes, drained sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over first layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: bacon cheese appetizers
directions: Slice bacon in half. Cut Cheddar cheese in small even cubes. Sprinkle cheese cubes with dash of cayenne pepper. Wrap bacon slices around each cheese cube. Fasten with wooden picks. Place on baking sheet or in an ovenproof glass dish. Broil for about 5 minutes, turning over after about 3 minutes or until cheese starts to melt and bacon is cooked to your liking. Garnish with cherry tomatoes. Serve as an appetizer with celery or carrot sticks or tortilla or other chips.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Place water in mixer bowl.
Add flour, dry milk, sugar, salt and oil.
Blend together for 45 seconds on low speed.
Sprinkle yeast over center of bowl.
Mix on medium speed for 10 minutes until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Spray Pam on top of dough and sides of bowl.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes or until dough doubles.
Punch down and make out dough balls size of walnut.
Proof until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush with butter.
Makes about 42 rolls.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add onions before or after cooking.
Slice sausage roll and add slices to cooked rice.
Cook until sausage is hot; serve.
Good with wheat rolls and salad.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: olive dip
directions: Dice olives and onions.
Blend other ingredients together with a fork.

title: payday cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and dissolve peanut butter in mixture.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into shallow pan.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: ham and cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper, blending until smooth.
Add water and cook until mixture comes to boil, stirring constantly.
Add cabbage.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in ham and cook until heated through.
Blend in sour cream. Heat but do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: pretzel salad(recipe originated from daughter, cheryl)
directions: Line a 9 x 1-inch pan with mixture of pretzels, oleo and 4 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool.
Combine the next 3 ingredients and spread over cooked crust.
Mix the remaining ingredients and let thicken slightly.
Pour over cream mixture and refrigerate.
Set out 1/2 hour before serving.
Cut into squares. Serves 12.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Cook rice in 5 cups boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Set aside.
Cook onions in butter in large skillet until limp, but not browned.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Make the cake according to package directions, except using 3 eggs instead of 2, and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Leave in pan to cool.
When the cake is cool, pour the pineapple over it.
Spread to distribute evenly.
Mix the cream cheese with the large package of pudding and the 2 cups milk.
Spread mixture over cake.
Spread the Cool Whip over all and refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, add other ingredients and work until
soft
dough.
Put
in large, greased bowl.
Cover with
wet dish towel.
Let set overnight at room temperature. Make into rolls two
hours before meal time.	Let rise.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt in saucepan, stirring over low heat, the butter and chocolate.
When chocolate has melted, add cocoa, sugar, cream and salt.
Stir to combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil slowly. Immediately remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla.
Warm in microwave before using.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Combine corn and green beans in greased 2-quart baking dish. Mix soup, sour cream, onion and cheese in bowl.
Spoon evenly over vegetables.
Mix butter, cracker crumbs and almonds in bowl. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices and water.
Pour into punch bowl and add ice cubes. Just before serving, pour in sodas.
Top with fruit ring mold.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, dash of salt and melted oleo.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Decorate top with pecan halves.
Cook at 350° for about 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when sticking into center of pie.
Cool to serve.

title: chicken vegetable stew
directions: Place chicken, 3/4 cup broth, seasonings and garlic in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

Add vegetables and remaining 1/2 cup chicken broth. Replace cover and cook on low heat until chicken and vegetables are done, 45 to 50 minutes. Add lemon juice. Serve in bowls. Garnish with chopped parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix and eggs as directed on the package.
Bake in 2 layers.
Cool.
Place first layer on cake plate.
Spread 1/2 can pineapple and 1/2 coconut over first layer.
Cover with 1/2 recipe of Seven Minute Frosting.
Add second layer.
Repeat with coconut, pineapple and frosting, reserving a little coconut for garnish. Frost entire cake with remaining frosting and sprinkle with coconut.

title: heavenly broiled fish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl; set aside.
Place fish in single layer on well-greased broiler pan.
Brush fish with lemon juice.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 4 to 6 minutes.
Remove from broiler and spread mixture on fillets.
Broil 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into cottage cheese in long glass 8 x 11 1/2-inch 2-quart dish.
Add drained pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt margarine. Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika, salt and pepper.
Heat the butter in a very hot skillet.
Add meat, stirring to separate the pieces to cook evenly, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove the meat with slotted spoon.
Add onion; saute for 1 minute.
Add the wine; cook down to reduce by half.
Lower the heat.
Add the sour cream, stirring (do not allow cream to boil, or it will curdle).
Return meat to pan.
Serve with noodles.

title: mint brownies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter, eggs, sugar, vanilla and Hershey's syrup.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour mixture and nuts to creamed mixture.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sandies
directions: Mix the margarine and sugar in a mixing bowl for 4 minutes. Add vanilla, flour and water; mix for 2 minutes.
Add pecans. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar while still hot.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: zoe's pineapple-apple surprise
directions: Mix flour, egg, vinegar and pineapple juice and cook until thick; cool.
Pour pineapple over diced apples to keep from turning brown.
Pour cooked sauce over apples and pineapple.
Add nuts and whipped topping.
Stir well.
Chill.

title: cioppino
directions: Soak and scrub clams; let soak in water until ready to use. Heat olive oil in a 6-quart pot.
Brown celery, potatoes, carrot, parsley, garlic and onion; stir often.
Cut fish about 1-inch wide, add to vegetable mixture with crushed tomatoes and cook for 20 minutes.
Add broth, water and bay leaves.
Keep heat high enough to keep mixture bubbling.
Stir occasionally.
Add salt and all spices.
After 10 minutes, add clams and wine; cook 5 minutes. Add crab and shrimp; cook another 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in butter.
Serve with sourdough bread or pour over white rice.
May also be served with green salad and pasta.

title: peppermint candy
directions: Melt almond bark according to package directions.
Stir in crushed peppermints.
Quickly spread onto a sheet of wax paper. When cool, break into pieces.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese and onions.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.

title: breakfast taco
directions: Butter flour tortillas.
Add scrambled eggs, bacon or ham, cheese and picante sauce.
Roll like a burrito.
Cook 45 seconds in microwave.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Mix macaroni, onion, ham, salt and mayonnaise.
Consistency should be a little liquid but not too liquid.
Toss broccoli and 1/2 of cheese into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add remainder of cheese.
Cook for additional 5 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salts, garlic and pepper.
Shape meatballs.
Place in ungreased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: new netherlands cole slaw
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients to boiling in saucepan.
Add some of the hot mixture to the slightly beaten egg, then stir into the hot vinegar in saucepan.
Cook until mixture thickens and boils. Remove from heat.
Beat in 2 tablespoons cream.
(I use milk instead of cream.)
Pour while hot over 3 cups finely shredded cabbage.
Chill; serve cold.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put in mixing bowl the sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix at low speed, slowly but steadily and add coffee, milk and oil which was mixed in a quart jar.
Stop mixer, scrape sides and bottom, turn on again and add eggs and vanilla.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in oleo. Add hamburger and brown. Drain.
Add flour, soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add soup, bouillon and sour cream.
Heat; sprinkle with parsley. Serve over noodles.

title: hot potato salad with hash browns
directions: Place all ingredients, except potatoes, in a large bowl and mix.
Now add potatoes and mix well.
(It's easier to add potatoes last.)
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with parsley or paprika.

title: heavenly rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, marshmallows, pineapple, cherries and nuts in a bowl.
Chill the evaporated milk in freezer tray until soft ice forms around edges (about 15 or 20 minutes).
Then whip it until stiff, 1 minute.
Add lemon juice; whip 2 more minutes until very stiff.
Beat in sugar.
Fold into rice mixture.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Let cool and cut into strips.
Cook broccoli by directions on box.
In a 13 x 9 inch
pan,
layer chicken and broccoli.
Mix soups, egg,
mayonnaise, and cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with dressing mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Heat milk in a large pan. When hot, pour in paste.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla. Wonderful over biscuits!

title: orange dribble cake
directions: Mix together eggs, cake mix, pudding, cold water, oil and salt.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
While cooling, make sauce. Heat together powdered sugar, orange juice, water and butter over double boiler until well mixed.
Poke holes in cake with fork and pour sauce over cake.
Heat sifted powdered sugar and lemon juice to boiling and pour over warm cake.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll in small balls in sugar and flatten with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Enjoy!

title: english pea casserole
directions: Drain 1 can of peas.
Place in bottom of a large casserole dish. Layer 2 1/2 boiled eggs and 1/2 can mushroom soup.
Cover with sliced cheese. Stand saltine crackers up around inside of casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick oleo in pan.
Crumble up enough crackers to take up liquid oleo.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk and pudding.
Mix together pudding mixture with cheese, butter and sugar mixture.
When smooth and blended well, fold in nondairy whipped cream.
In plastic flowerpot, put layer of crushed cookies, then layer of filling.
Alternate layers so that top is finished with crushed cookies (looks like potting soil).
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Place a silk flower or flowers in center and use a plastic shovel for serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in thin slices.
Mince garlic very fine.
Saute zucchini and garlic very slowly in oil in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook until tender.
Beat eggs with rotary beater.
Add milk and Parmesan cheese.
Beat thoroughly; season with salt and pepper.
Pour over zucchini and lift slices gently so egg mixture gets to bottom of pan.
Cover and continue to cook over low heat until eggs are set.
This can also be cooked in a very slow oven.
Slice in pie shaped wedges and serve hot. Serves 6.
Good with tossed salad, garlic bread and fish.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Mix well and pour into 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container at room temperature. For each serving, stir 4 level teaspoonfuls mixture into 3/4 cup water in cup or mug.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Yields 16 servings.
Contains 30 calories per cup.

title: caramel apple delight
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients using electric mixer.
Use as a dip for apples.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cross orchards old fashioned sorghum cake
directions: Heat butter and sorghum to a boil.
Stir in ginger and spices. Stir in soda.
Take from fire and add sour milk and beaten egg. Beat well.
Add flour sifted three or four times.
Beat again, hard.
Bake in loaf pan 8 x 8-inch or two small square cake pans. Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour vegetables
directions: Slice and simmer the vegetables for 25 minutes in covered frypan.
After cooking 10 minutes, slice the apple over the vegetables.
Pour vegetables into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour the sweet 'n sour sauce over top.
Put in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Best with fish or chicken.

title: squash souffle
directions: Boil squash, drain and mash.
Add onion, milk, eggs, cheese, butter and salt.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit bowl salad
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add Cool Whip and almond extract; whip until firm.
Set aside.
In a clear, glass bowl or trifle bowl, layer blueberries, then peach slices, strawberries and 1/2 of the yogurt mixture.
Layer grapes and mandarin oranges.
Top with remaining yogurt mixture.
Garnish with strawberries and raspberries.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with vegetables and/or chips.

title: joanne's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones, discarding skin and bones. Chop chicken. Stir together chicken and remaining ingredients. Spoon evenly into 2 lightly greased 8 x 8-inch baking dishes (or one 9 x 13-inch dish). Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: dill bread
directions: Mix dry yeast and lukewarm water together; let sit for 5 minutes.
Heat cottage cheese and soda.
Mix butter, dill seed, salt, flour, sugar and onion powder.
Add yeast and cottage cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients without wieners and boil, add wieners and simmer 40 minutes.

title: mom's pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 1 package pistachio pudding.
Put aside in bowl.
Mix eggs and club soda.
Then mix both together until blended.
Beat with mixer 4 minutes on medium speed.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes.
Cool and frost. Sprinkle either coconut or crushed nuts or cherries, if desired, although not necessary.

title: homemade ice cream cones
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over hot water, stirring occasionally.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Stir gently to coat well.
Pack, with greased hands, into 12 greased custard cups leaving centers hollow.
Cool thoroughly.
Remove from cups and fill with ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge ice cream
directions: Mix together all ingredients and taste.
You may want to add a little more syrup and sugar.
Pour in churn.
Finish filling to line with homogenized milk and freeze.

title: r.j.'s easy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine the juice of 1 lemon with olive oil and thyme in shallow bowl.
Marinate chicken breasts in lemon mixture 10 minutes to 1 hour (depending on time available!).
Bake in nonstick pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Lay 1 to 2 slices of tomato on each breast. Cover tomato with cheese. Bake for approximately 10 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp clam ball
directions: Mix, chill and serve with crackers.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Cook meat, onion and celery until celery is tender.
Add soups, water and noodles.
Bake for 3/4 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: grilled chicken in vinegar sauce
directions: Grill chickens.
Pull meat and skins off bones.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Top with crumbled Ritz crackers or can use crumbled bacon.

title: lace cookies
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Grease and flour well a cookie sheet.
In large skillet combine all ingredients; heat, stirring over low heat until mixture is mushy.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake 5 or 6 minutes.
Remove one at a time quickly.
Roll up around wooden spoon handle.
(They get crisp when cool and you have to work fast when taking them off sheet.)
Also, don't bake too long.
They'll be slightly brown and soft when you take them out and they run together easily if you put too much, too close on sheet.

title: pork balls with sauerkraut and carrots
directions: Combine
first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Layer carrots, potatoes and sauerkraut in pot.
Sprinkle with caraway. Pour
broth
on top.
Bring to boil.
Lower temperature.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Slice chilies longways.
Put cheese into or on each chili.
Put in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Whisk eggs, milk and flour well and pour over stuffed chilies.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: english trifle
directions: Crumble pound cake in large bowl.
Make Jell-O; drain fruit cocktail and add to Jell-O.
Pour Jell-O and fruit over pound cake. Refrigerate until Jell-O is set.
Slice kiwi fruit and arrange around inside of bowl.
Make pudding and pour a layer over Jell-O and fruit.
Slice strawberries and arrange on top of pudding, then add a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle blueberries on top of Cool Whip.
Cover with remaining pudding, then layer sliced banana over pudding and cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with any leftover fruit, if desired.
This may also be made with other variations of fruit, depending on what is in season.

title: burger noodle bake
directions: Brown meat lightly in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add onion; cook until tender (not brown).
Add soup, cheese, sugar and seasoning.
Simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles in separate pot.
When done, add drained noodles to sauce. Combine then turn into a 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch casserole. Sprinkle cornflake crumbs and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat milk and egg together.
Add pumpkin, sugar, spices and flour. Bake in a single crust at 375° for 1 hour or until firm in the middle.

title: ice cream cupcakes
directions: Scoop centers from cakes; fill with ice cream.
Beat egg whites with honey added gradually until stiff.
Cover tops with honey meringue, piling it high over ice cream.
Brown quickly in a preheated oven at 425°.
Serve immediately.

title: low calorie "cream" sauce base
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor or blender.
Add any choice of favorite herbs or salt substitute.
Use by the tablespoons as low calorie thickening for soups, sauces, stews and other dishes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: butterfinger nuggets
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips
and peanut butter in microwave or double boiler.
Mix well, then add cereal and powdered sugar. Form nuggets and eat.

title: carrot pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake until done, about 35 minutes, at 400°.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: makloubeli(main dish)
directions: Peel
and
cut eggplant,
then	fry.
Boil
meat
until tender.
Keep the boiling
water.
In
a 5-quart saucepan, put the meat, then the fried eggplant.
Wash
cups of rice with water, then put it over
the eggplant.
Add allspice and salt. Add 3 cups of water (the one you boiled the meat with).
Bring to a boil. Then over medium
heat,
cook
until rice is done. In a serving tray, turn	the
contents of the saucepan upside-down and eat! Add fried pine nuts on top.
Bon appetit!

title: almond pistachio ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and freeze.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: scottish short bread
directions: Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine well and chill. Garnish with orange slices.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix together and put stuffing in pork chops.
Put together with toothpicks and cover and cook at 300° for about 1 hour, or until done.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms, cutting the ends of the stems off.
Set aside.
Place remaining ingredients except bell pepper in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add the mushrooms and bell pepper. Bring to a boil again. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until the mushrooms are tender. Cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate in covered container for several hours before serving.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Break crab meat into chunks.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Heat mixture in double boiler until heated through.
Spoon into chafing dish. Serve with melba toast.

title: triple good bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles; cool.
Beat margarine with sugar; add vanilla, oats, flour, walnuts, soda and salt.
Reserve 2 cups and press remaining onto bottom of prepared pan.
Spread raisin mixture and then sprinkle reserved 2 cups mixture on top.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, salt, soda, cinnamon, cloves and lemon zest.
Mix well with a wire whisk.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter together in a large bowl using an electric mixer.
Add egg, applesauce and honey and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add the flour mixture, fresh apple and raisins and blend at low speed until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Dough will quite soft.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart. If you wish, sprinkle the cookies with oats.
Bake 23 to 25 minutes.

title: microwave mexicali nachos
