directions: Spread cream cheese in 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Layer chili, green chilies, green pepper and onion on cream cheese.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix well; shape and chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease two loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
Place all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well in center and add oil, vanilla and eggs. Mix with a spoon.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Pour into pans and bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool before removing from pans.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9
x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Place pineapple, cherries and nuts in pan.
(Do not mix.)
Spread dry cake mix over mixture evenly.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken kelley
directions: Soak chicken in eggs for 2 hours, then dip breasts in bread crumbs (seasoned with seasoned salt, garlic powder, paprika and pepper).
Brown chicken in melted margarine for 2 minutes on each side; drain.
In buttered casserole (9 x 12-inch), place chicken; top with mushrooms.
Cover each breast with 2 slices Muenster. Pour chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, Miracle Whip and rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: president eisenhower's favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Pat into 9 1/2 to 10-inch square pan (at least 2-inches deep).
Bake at 375° until sides pull away, approximately 1/2-inch (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: chicken and asparagus
directions: Partially cook asparagus; drain.
Place in a greased baking dish.
In a skillet over medium heat, brown chicken in oil on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken over asparagus.	In bowl, mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes at 375°, until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and chill for 1 1/2 to 2 hours and serve.
Use 1/2 watermelon as serving bowl.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add enough water to the juice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and ginger. Gradually stir in the 2 1/2 cups juice with the vinegar and soy sauce.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until desired thickness.

Add pineapple, green pepper strips, onion, carrots and chicken; cover and place back in the microwave on High for another 20 minutes or until the vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring every 5 minutes.
Serve with hot, cooked rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions.

Add enough flour to make a roux. Slowly add chicken broth then half and half, stirring constantly. Add seafood (I suggest precooking seafood in case milk doesn't get hot enough to cook completely; I precook in the microwave).
Cook very slowly, do not boil.
Since the seafood is precooked it is only necessary to simmer to get the bisque good and hot.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together; add rest of ingredients. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pesto lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Butter a 2-quart shallow baking dish and spread the cooked spaghetti in it. Stir the nutmeg and sherry into the warm Veloute Sauce and set aside. Melt the butter in a skillet; add the mushrooms and cook, stirring until soft. Spoon half the sauce over the spaghetti. Place the chicken/broccoli and mushrooms on top and spoon on the remaining sauce. Sprinkle with the grated cheese and bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy toffee
directions: Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Place saltine crackers in single layer until pan is full.
Combine brown sugar and butter; microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir thoroughly and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with chocolate chips.
As chips melt, spread with spatula and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill for 30 minutes. Break into small bite size pieces.

title: cauliflower spinach salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl to make a dressing. Combine last 4 ingredients in a large bowl and add dressing. Toss to coat.

title: rum cake(bacardi rum)
directions: Spray
Bundt
pan
with Pam; add nuts in and press them down. Mix
remaining
ingredients
and pour over nuts in pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: city chicken legs
directions: Remove fat from chops.
Place on medium size skewers after cutting meat up.
Roll meat on the skewers in flour.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Place meat in a covered dish.
Add wine or chicken broth to the dish, about 1/2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check to see that liquid does not cook away.
If so, add more.
Cook until tender.
Enjoy!

title: south-of-the-border nacho ball
directions: Place popped corn into zip top bag and seal. With rolling pin, crush popped corn to medium fine consistency.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, blend processed cheese, cream cheese and black olives until smooth. Shape cheese mixture into ball.
In a shallow dish, combine crushed popcorn with chili powder or paprika.
Roll cheese ball in mixture until completely coated. Garnish with tortilla chips.
Makes one 5-inch ball.

title: enchiladas(double for a 9 x 13-inch pan)
directions: Brown beef with 1 tablespoon onion, green pepper and garlic. Drain grease.
Add Mexican tomatoes, oregano, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: wiener dip
directions: Empty 12 ounces cottage cheese in blender.
Take sharp knife and chop wieners on top of cheese.
If your fingers are not bleeding from chopping wieners, cut dill pickle in small pieces on top of previous goodies.
Now, put jalapenos in mixture.
Then add the seasoned salt and the vinegar.
Almost forgot, add the low-fat mayonnaise.
Put blender container on the electric mechanism and turn on to about speed 4. As the mixture begins to mix, use a spatula to help the mixture.
Caution:
Do not get spatula too far down.
You might have some metal in mixture.
When all mixture is same color, stop blender.
If your spatula is still intact, get a handful of crackers.
Put on mixture and eat until full.

title: filie delite cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pecans and melted butter.
Beat 1 egg in a large bowl.
Pour into long cake pan; flatten in pan.
Mix in a large bowl the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool overnight.
If during the day, 2 to 3 hours before cutting.

title: grandma's divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo at 260°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour sugar into egg whites in slow stream.
Add vanilla and beat until shine goes away (5 to 10 minutes).
Finish by hand. Add pecans and drop onto waxed paper.

title: fresh apple pancake
directions: Spray 10-inch cast-iron skillet with cooking spray and heat on medium heat. Have all ingredients at room temperature. Mix together the flour, sugar, salt, eggs, milk and 1 teaspoon butter; pour all at once into heated pan. Lay apple slices on top of mixture, arranging in an attractive pattern, completely covering the batter. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top of apple slices. Drizzle 1 tablespoon butter on top. Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until pancake puffs up. Cut into wedges and serve while warm.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil hen in salted water until tender enough to strip from bone. Cool hen; strip meat from bone. Boil spaghetti according to directions, using enough broth from hen to cover. Simmer celery, onion, pepper and garlic until tender. Combine with meat and spaghetti. Add cheese and other ingredients; mix well and moisten with enough broth to make the mixture slightly "soupy." This will keep well in refrigerator or freezer. Reserve the rest of the chicken broth to add to mixture if you plan to store in refrigerator or freezer. Serves 12 to 15.

title: george washington gingerbread
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together.
Beat eggs; add sugar, molasses and oil; mix until creamy.
Add flour mixture and cream well.
Last, dissolve soda in boiling water and stir into mixture. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: paradise cran-apple sauce
directions: In covered saucepan, simmer cranberries in water for 20 minutes or until tender. Press through a sieve or cheesecloth. Return to saucepan. Add apples; cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender but firm. Add sugar. Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking. Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an oven proof pan. Bake at 350 F for 10-15 minutes or until cheese melts.
This may also be cooked in a microwave oven until it is heated through.

title: sausage and rice pilaf
directions: Cook sausage over low heat in a large skillet, pouring off grease, now and then, and stirring to crumble meat.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in soup and cooked rice.
Pour into casserole dish, cover and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients above and chill until firm.
Mix next 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool and spread on firm jello. Mix last 2 ingredients and spread over cooked mixture.
Grate 1/2 cup cheddar cheese and spread over top of mixture and chill.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and pick from bone (set aside).
Melt in a pan the Cheez Whiz, margarine and mushroom soup.
Mix broccoli, celery, onion, rice and chicken in a casserole; pour melted Cheez Whiz, margarine and soup over it. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: omigosh omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook bacon.
Drain grease and set aside.
Chop tomato and onion in large cast iron frypan.
Brown hash browns. Line frypan with hash browns.
Layer bacon on hash browns.
Combine milk and egg and scramble mixture.
Pour egg and milk mixture over potatoes and bacon and cook until mix starts to firm up on bottom.
Add all other ingredients and bake until firm. Test with toothpick.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: For dressing, combine the sour cream, lemon juice, honey and cinnamon.
Toss the fruit together, then spoon into a sherbet or dessert glass.
Spoon dressing over fruit.
Serves 3.

title: beef in a blanket
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in small amount of fat in skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Break up with fork.
Combine biscuit mix and milk.
Stir to blend.
Roll out on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Drain excess fat from meat mixture.
Spread meat mixture evenly over dough.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Moisten edges of dough and seal edges securely.
Brush top with butter. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Mix soup with 1/3 can of milk and peas.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over and serve with beef roll, sliced.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all 3 ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container until needed.
Use about 1 tablespoon per cup of hot water.
Makes about 32 servings.

title: white icing
directions: Cook flour and milk in a saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Cool.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a small, heavy-bottom saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook for a few minutes, until golden. Add milk and stir with wire whisk until sauce is thickened. Remove from heat.
Pour a small amount of the sauce into the bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole.
Layer potatoes, onion and white sauce in casserole.
Place pork chops on top of potato mixture.
Cover and bake for about 1 1/4 hours.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: special pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and oranges with juice.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each one.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until it tests done. Cool.
Combine pineapple, juices, pudding mix and whipped topping. Spread over cake and between layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: light p.b.c.(punch bowl cake)
directions: You will need 1 large clear bowl.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Rinse macaroni.
Mix ingredients together and top with Italian dressing to taste.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Turn mixture out into a ball and roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Add cinnamon while rolling out mixture to prevent it from sticking.
Use holiday shaped cookie cutters to make ornaments.
Use tip of pencil to make small holes in tops of ornaments to hang them up later.
Let ornaments dry on tray for several days, turning them over with a spatula twice daily.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: In skillet, combine butter, sugar, vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add cabbage; cover and cook for at least 10 minutes.
Add apples, if desired.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Keeps well under refrigeration.

title: seedless grape salad
directions: Melt the cream cheese, sugar, salad dressing and lemon juice over a low heat to soften. Mix with the grapes and marshmallows, chill and serve.

title: maple bluff chicken
directions: Dot chicken with butter. Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle over chicken. Don't cover or turn chicken. Bake 3 hours at 300°. Its SO GOOD.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix again.

Mix in oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut. Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; mix in. Make into small balls. Place onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour over row of bananas, then row of vanilla wafers in bowl or pan.
Cover with beaten egg whites and brown.

title: quick desserts
directions: Beat egg slowly for 1 minute; add sugar.
Beat until smooth. Set aside.
Mix other ingredients together.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes.
Good with vanilla ice cream.

title: dove with dressing
directions: Note:
Prepare quantity of dressing and dove according to amount of people being fed.
If feeding 6 or more, increase nuts and applesauce.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake 50 minutes at 325° or until top is brown.
Don't salt.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the meat; drain excess fat.
Add the next 7 ingredients. Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse. Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.

title: almond bake
directions: Mix flour with meat.
Brown and cook until tender in 1/4 pound butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook 2 cups rice according to directions.
Add rice and beaten eggs to meat; add soups.
Melt 3/4 pound butter; add cracker crumbs.
Line pans with crumb mixture, saving some for the top.
Put sliced almonds on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan and an 8 x 11-inch pan. Serves 20.
Freezes well.

title: chunky salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes; save juice.
Put tomatoes and jalapenos in food processor.
Add tomato juice for moisture, a little at a time, to desired mixture.
Saute onions, celery and peppers in olive oil until tender.
Do not overcook.
Let cool.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into jars and seal.
Make about 4 to 5 quarts.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken
breasts
and
then
cut into small pieces (squares).	Cut up celery and oranges and add to chicken, then add pineapple.	Use
mayonnaise,
enough
to hold together the ingredients.
Top
with
almonds.
Let stand for several hours before
serving.
Serve with banana slices (halves lengthwise) topped with
crushed
salted
nuts.
Arrange
banana slices on side of
plate
with
salad in the middle.	Cheese biscuits go very well with this.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Put marshmallows and milk in saucepan over a slow fire and heat until marshmallows are melted.
Do not boil.
Cool.
Add whipped cream, nuts and pineapple and stir well.
Pour into a dish lined with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate to chill.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar and water until there is a crackling sound in water.
Slowly pour into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until it holds in peaks.
Pour onto a buttered platter.

title: kathye's strawberry cheese mold
directions: Mix everything together except jam. Line a mold with Saran Wrap. Heat jam until melted and pour into mold, then add cheese mixture. Cover and refrigerate. Flip it out of the mold onto a plate. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole - kentucky
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on bag.
Drain well.
Melt half-stick of butter and mix with cheese.
Mix this into cooked broccoli.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and half stick of melted butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter together.
Press into bottom of a pan.
Combine corn syrup and peanut butter and set aside.
Put half the ice cream on top of the crust and then drizzle with half of the syrup mixture.
Then add the remaining ice cream and syrup mixture. You can drizzle chocolate syrup on top, if desired, and sprinkle with peanuts.
Cover with aluminum foil and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: easy fudgy pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
In medium bowl, combine baking mix and cocoa; stir in 1 cup sweetened condensed milk, 1/4 cup syrup and vanilla until blended.
Spoon evenly into prepared pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining sweetened condensed milk, remaining 1/2 cup syrup and hot water. Pour liquid mixture carefully over top of mixture in pan.
Do not stir.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set and cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes, spooning pudding from bottom of pan over top. Serve warm; garnish with whipped topping or ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Be sure to drain spinach very well.
You can squeeze it dry by hand to get all the water out.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Coat an 8-inch square pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Put peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until butter melts and chocolate chips look soft and glossy, but still retain their shape.
Stir until smooth, then stir in marshmallows.
Microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds. Marshmallows will be slightly melted.
Stir to mix, then stir in cereal until well blended.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell 10 minutes at 375°.
Layer tomatoes in pie shell and sprinkle with dry ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread over top of pie.
Bake 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pina colada
directions: Mix rum, cream of coconut and pineapple juice in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour into glasses filled with cracked ice and garnish with pineapple spears.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: dang good pie
directions: Add all ingredients to melted oleo.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: overnight italian omelet
directions: Spray a 14 x 11-inch pan with oil.
Put bread on bottom. Drizzle with margarine.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese, Mozzarella cheese and salami on top.

title: honey mustard wings
directions: Combine margarine, honey, mustard, curry and salt in small saucepan.
Heat on low flame.
Place chicken wings in shallow baking pan; sprinkle with curry and a dash of pepper.
Pour sauce mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and baste every 15 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and pour in the baking dish.
Pour the fruit over the crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
When done, the crust will be on top and the fruit will be on the bottom.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: charming cherry buds
directions: Mix well and pat in pan.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: egg bread for muffins, corn sticks, or bread
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees. Grease and heat pan. Beat egg and add milk and shortening. Blend in meal and sugar. Pour into hot greased pan. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 14 muffins, 18 sticks or 1 medium size skillet of bread.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Precook spinach; drain well.
Stir in cheese, onion, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown and pie seems set.

title: tuna pepper appetizers
directions: Halve, seed and rinse peppers.
Drain on paper towel.
Drain tuna and flake.
Mix with cream cheese; add onion and garlic salt to taste.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
These are quite spicy but delicious.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine crab meat, mayo, soup, Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add shrimp and crab meat mixture.
Add stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Cook Pinto Beans with Ham Hock till done.
Remove Ham Hock. Cook remainder of ingredients and add to beans and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Combine unbeaten egg whites, sugar, water, and corn syrup in top of double boiler. Beat just enough to blend ingredients. Place over rapidly boiling water and beat with hand mixer until mixture is light and fluffy and will hold its shape. This requires 7 minutes by hand or 3 to 4 minutes by electric mixer. Remove from heat; add vanilla and continue beating until frosting is stiff enough to stand in peaks. Spread on cake and enjoy!

title: baked steak(from gourmet magazine)
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Rub steak well with garlic.
Brown fast in skillet on both sides.
Salt and pepper on both sides.
(This can be done ahead of time.)
Place on broiler rack.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes for medium rare.
Take drippings and pour into pan.
Add wine and butter.

title: bar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter; add eggs.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Roll 1/4 dough on lightly floured board in rectangle shape.
Cut into strips 4 1/4-inches wide.
Spread raspberry jam down the center of each, 1 1/2-inches wide.
Cool strips in freezer 5 minutes.
Fold sides over jam; with wide spatula place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 11 minutes.
Cut into bars when cooled.

title: vanilla ice cream(tastes like dairy queen ice cream)
directions: Mix together with egg beater.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: seafood enchiladas
directions: Combine taco sauce and sour cream.
In blender, combine cottage cheese, milk, garlic and salt.
Spread 1 tablespoon sauce mixture over tortillas.
Top with cheese, seafood and remaining green onions.
Spoon remaining taco sauce mix in greased 12 x 7-inch baking pan.
Roll up tortillas and place seam side down.
Pour cottage cheese over mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved green onions and olives.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and beat until fluffy.
If desired, use electric mixer at medium speed.
Sift flour and salt into butter mixture.
Blend thoroughly with hands.
Knead gently so dough gets a "thinly layered" look.
Separate into two balls, press into flat, round shape.
Wrap in plastic or wax paper and refrigerate until chilled.
Roll out on floured surface 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into shapes; prick with fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.
Bake at 325°.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: In a large bowl, put first six ingredients.
Stir well.
Put yeast in a cup; add 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir yeast-water and add to bowl.
Add 5 cups of bread flour.
Stir.
Add more flour as needed, so it will not be sticky.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Must be able to hear bubbles of yeast snapping.
Let rise several hours.

title: corky's picnic dinner
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Brown hamburger and onion. Drain.
Add all ingredients to cooked noodles.
Save 1/2 of cheese for topping casserole.
Cook until bubbly and cheese topping is browned.

title: quick pizza snack
directions: Slice the English muffins.
Spread with small amount of sauce. Sprinkle with spices and cheese.
Add any other topping of your choice.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix avocado with picante sauce and set aside.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix and set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer ingredients in the following order: refried beans with chilies, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Top with cheese.
Serve with traditional flavored Tostitos.
Keeps up to 3 days in the refrigerator. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, Karo syrup, butter, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Stuff in pecans until you can't stuff any more.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until center is firm.
Cool to room temperature before cutting.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine garlic powder, salt and pepper. Rub chicken with mixture. Beat egg yolk with honey and 2 tablespoons butter in small bowl. Brush chicken with honey mixture.
Place, skin side up, in greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, basting with remaining butter. Turn and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer until brown.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix and let stand overnight; put in sterilized jars and process 20 minutes in hot water bath at simmering.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Chop beef. Add all ingredients and heat on low until cream cheese is smooth. Serve with crackers.

title: choco-oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter, margarine and vegetable oil until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla. Add combined flour, oats and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press until 1/4-inch thick circles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are brown.
Remove to wire rack. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: If using boiled shrimp, which have been seasoned, chop shrimp and mix all ingredients.
If using raw shrimp, cook with 1/2 cup water and add salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce to taste until all water is evaporated, then chop.
Mix with remaining ingredients.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate raw sweet potato into milk to keep them from turning dark.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Pour into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: On cookie sheet, separate crescent rolls.
Butter one side of each triangle.
Sprinkle enough cinnamon chips on each triangle to cover.
Roll each triangle at short side.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and debone.
Make layer of all chicken meat in buttered casserole dish.
Spread soup over chicken and cornbread. Mix over soup.
Pour 1 cup of broth over all.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: (No salt, except that in soup.)

title: apricot raisin bars
directions: Combine first ingredients in mixing bowl and set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, apple pie spice and salt.
Add to molasses mixture stirring well.
Stir in raisins and apple. Spread mixture in 9-inch square pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Let cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: layered pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts and pat into bottom of 9x13 inch pan.
Microwave on high for 3 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup cool whip and spread into pan.
Beat pudding and milk and pour over mixture in pan.
Spread remaining cool whip over top and refrigerate.

title: salmon loaf for two
directions: Grease a loaf pan.
Blend egg into flaked salmon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is crisp and brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: quick chicken stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, mix the soup mix and water.
While it's coming to a boil, cut chicken into thin strips.
When liquid comes to a boil, continue boiling for 1 minute until slightly thickened. Add chicken and vegetables.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, until chicken is done.
Serve with hot rice or noodles.

title: bea's irish spring
directions: Fill Collins glass with crushed ice. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Add orange slice and cherry garnish.

title: italian meat balls with italian sausage
directions: Cut casing of Italian
sausage.
Mix with ground chuck. Cut celery, onions and garlic
fine or blend lightly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into medium size meat balls.
Bake in oven 30 minutes at 350°.
Cook in tomato sauce.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: never fail caramel icing
directions: Mix butter, brown and white sugar and cream.
Bring to a boil and cook rapidly for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows.
When they have melted, add vanilla and sifted confectioners sugar.
Stir until thick enough to spread over layers of cake.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Bake pie shells until lightly brown.
Mash potatoes until very smooth.
Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup sugar, butter, egg yolks, spices, flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Use electric mixer; beat until light and fluffy, about 5 to 7 minutes.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold egg white mixture into potato mixture.
Pour filling into browned pie shells.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Makes two pies.

title: chow chow
directions: Sprinkle a handful of salt over tomatoes, onions, peppers and cabbage and let it set overnight.
Drain well and add to the following mixture:

title: northwest cherry salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve as a condiment with chicken, turkey or pork.

title: whipped cream salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar and flour in top of double boiler; add remaining ingredients except cream and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
When cool fold in whipped cream.
Makes 2 cups. Excellent dressing for Waldorf Salad.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Cook broccoli in water until unfrozen and drain.
In a large saucepan, saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Add cheese and soup.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and simmer until all is blended well; stir often while cooking dip.
Serve hot with chips, veggies, etc.

title: pepperkakor
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and syrup.
Roll out cookies and bake in 325° oven about 10 minutes.

title: mexican sausage
directions: Brown pork sausage in skillet or Dutch oven.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix lemonade, sugar and boiling water.
Add other juices. Freeze in ice cream buckets.
Take out of freezer 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale to each bucket of slush.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix sugar, spices, shortening, molasses, salt and eggs.
Add soda, dissolved in 2 tablespoons water.
Let dough stand for 10 minutes.
Form into small balls.
Drop on cookie sheet; flatten each ball and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Heat together cheese and soup. Pour over vegetables and mushrooms.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake, covered, 350° for 45 minutes.
Last 10 minutes put onions on top and finish baking.

title: oatmeal-peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour, salt and soda.
Add vanilla.
Stir in quick oats and chocolate morsels or raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: southwestern vegetable soup
directions: Place tomatoes in blender container.
Process on puree for 10 seconds.
Pour into a large container.
Add chicken broth, cabbage, onions, green beans and carrots.
Mix well to combine. Stir in chili seasoning.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.
Freezes well.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Drain peaches; reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Arrange peaches in deep 10-inch greased pie pan.
Cream butter or margarine; add egg, then milk, flour, baking powder, flour and pudding.
Cover peaches with batter.
Cream together cream cheese, peach juice and sugar.
Spread over batter to within 1-inch of sides.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Wash rice and drain. Place in greased casserole dish. Add soups and water. Place pork chops on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: peach shortcake
directions: Drain peaches.
Prepare any recipe of biscuits.
Dip each cut biscuit in melted butter, dip in sugar mixture, sprinkle nuts on top.
Place sliced peaches around and on biscuits.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken lickin' wing dings
directions: Snip off tips of chicken wings.
Cut at elbow.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes with marinade poured over.

title: tomato zucchini nibbles
directions: Cut slice off bottom of cherry tomatoes so they will sit flat. Cut thin slice from top of tomatoes.
With small melon baller or spoon, carefully scoop out centers of tomatoes.
Sprinkle inside of tomatoes lightly with salt.
Combine zucchini, cottage cheese, chives and garlic salt.
Fill tomatoes using one rounded teaspoon in each.
Garnish each tomato with additional chives.
Makes 24 servings.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Arrange in large sized casserole the chicken first, then onion, tortillas (I like to cut them in strips), grated cheese and 1/2 of liquid mixture.
Repeat (layer 2 times).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Excellent!

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoon into hot deep fat. Cook until golden brown.
Don't make dough too thin.

title: pudding delight (lemon or chocolate)
directions: 1st layer:
Mix flour, melted butter and 1 cup pecan pieces in small bowl.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 15 minutes).
Cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute pepper in margarine. Add corn, egg and 1/2 onion rings.
Mix well.
Pour into medium baking dish. Bake, covered, for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with rest of onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes more. Serve hot!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup margarine and corn flakes. Pour into 15 x 11-inch greased casserole dish.
Mix the 1/4 cup margarine with corn flakes and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes a large casserole.
Use 1/2 recipe for smaller casserole.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Beat or blend all ingredients and use for dipping vegetables.

title: italian sausage with green peppers and onions
directions: Saute sausage in 2 tablespoons olive oil for about 15 minutes. Add onions, peppers, tomatoes, tomato sauce and all seasonings. Mix cornstarch with a little water to make paste.
Add to sauce. Cook mixture until sausage, peppers and onions are cooked.
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: date peanut loaf
directions: Place
dates
in small bowl;
sprinkle soda over dates. Cover with boiling water and set aside.
Cream brown sugar and shortening in
larger
bowl.
Add
salt and egg, beating well. Add peanuts and date mixture to this, mixing in well.
Stir in flour. Spoon into	a
x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1
hour or until done.
Yields 1 loaf.
(If salted peanuts are used, omit the salt in the recipe.)

title: mock pink champagne
directions: Mix sugar and water in saucepan; boil for 5 minutes.
Cool; add frozen concentrate. Refrigerate.
Chill for several hours.
At serving time, add ginger ale and grenadine syrup. Makes 20 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo, sugar and cheese.
Add eggs and extract alternately with flour.
Beat until mixed thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: debbie's chocolate layered dessert(sugar-free)
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
You can mix some Cool Whip Light with pudding to make a creamier dessert.
Spread remaining Cool Whip Light on top.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Roast for 10 minutes.
Stir, continue on "Roast" for 5 1/2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted; fold in marshmallow, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Boil noodles; drain. Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain. In large bowl, combine sauces, mushrooms, olives, spices and meat mixture. In crock-pot, layer sauce, noodles, pepperoni and cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are used. Cook on low for several hours. Makes a 5-quart crock-pot full.

title: chicken soup
directions: 1. Fry chicken until almost done. Cut into small pieces.
2. Finish frying with vegtables, seasonings, and butter.
3. Add all ingredients in a large pot. Add water to
desired consistency. Lightly boil for 5 minutes.

title: beef liver
directions: Put 3 tablespoons margarine or butter and onions in the pan. Fry until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove onions from pan.
Add 1/2 cup shortening until melted.
Coat beef liver with flour and fry until browned, about 2 or 3 minutes on each side.
Remove liver from pan; add 1 cup cold water and mushrooms.
Cook 1 minute.
Add bacon and onions.
Cook all together.
Put liver on top of onions.
Cover and simmer on top of stove, low heat, 30 minutes. Stir every 5 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, including greasing and flouring 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of prepared cake mix in the pan.
Cook 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: You may add peas, carrots, onions and green peppers.

title: dot's fudge
directions: Cook milk and cocoa over low heat until smooth. Add sugar, Karo and salt. Cook until soft-ball stage. Add butter and let cool until lukewarm, without stirring, then add vanilla and beat. Add nuts and pour into a buttered pan.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: bible fruit cake
directions: Roll in flour (1 Kings 4:22).
Season with spices (Chronicles 9:9).
Stir and bake in a deep pan in a slow oven.

title: linza(makes 2 pans)
directions: Add the above ingredients to the first mixture.
Mix well. Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll one part of the dough into each of the two baking sheets. 16 x 11 x 1 inch.
They may have to be pieced.

title: chicken and corn-pineapple salsa
directions: Season chicken with pepper. Heat 10 to 12 minutes until no pink is showing, turning once. Stir together corn, pineapple, sweet peppers, cilantro, jalapeno in a medium bowl. Serve with chicken.

title: make-ahead parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and cook until tender.
Mash with butter, cream cheese and milk until fluffy.
Beat in Parmesan, salt and white pepper to taste, then turn into a casserole dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Press plastic wrap onto the surface; cool briefly, then cover and refrigerate.

title: delicious salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except jello.
Sprinkle jello over other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: pork chops and rice bake
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in butter.
Spread uncooked rice in bottom of a rectangular baking dish.
Spread soup, onion and pimiento over rice.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Pour approximately 3 cups hot water over rice.
Place chops on top and cover tightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until pork chops and rice are done.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased bunt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Mix 1 cup confectioner sugar with lemon juice.
Put on cake and put back in over for a few minutes.

title: grandma zimmerman's apple butter
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in heavy baking dish (uncovered) at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
Do not stir.
Remove and stir well.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix 2 cups of white sugar with milk; boil for 5 minutes. Caramelize 1 cup of white sugar in iron skillet.
Add caramelized sugar to boiled mixture.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Use confectioners sugar to thicken icing as needed.

title: fresh apple spice cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture, beating well.
Stir in pecans and apples.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Using a toothpick, punch holes in cake while hot. Spoon glaze over cake.
Cool; remove from pan.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Pour off grease.
Lower heat; add other ingredients.
Add 1 can of water for 2 cans of soup.
May be frozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 loaf pans.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
In medium bowl, beat eggs and oil. Add zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients; stir well.
Bake 2 hours in angel food pan or 1 hour in loaf pans.
About 10 minutes before finished baking, spread with topping.
Return to oven for remaining 10 minutes.
Let cool before slicing.

title: el torito's sweet corn cakes
directions: Whip Crisco and butter until mixture becomes fluffy and creamy.
Gradually add masa and mix until well blended.
Add water gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Put corn kernels into blender and blend until coarsely chopped; stir into masa mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Now grate zucchini (do not grate zucchini ahead of time); if small zucchini is used, do not peel.
If large ones are used, use only the firm inside, no seeds or skin.
Add all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 or 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: love ya lion fudge
directions: In a large bowl, slowly blend sugar with melted butter.
Stir by hand until well blended.
Add peanut butter, cocoa, vanilla and walnuts if desired.
Mix until all ingredients are well blended. Press into a greased 8 x 12-inch pan or dish, using wax paper to press evenly in pan.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Combine above ingredients and chill. Form into ball shape and roll in chopped pecans.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Blend together; then add 1 small can Pet milk and 1 beaten egg. Blend as well as possible, then roll out into desired size.
Makes about 18 small pies.
I used 2 cups of self-rising flour and 1/2 cup plain.
No salt and no baking powder.

title: creamy banana dessert
directions: Cut flour
and margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal; stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Press flour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake
at
for
minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar, beating until fluffy.
Stir 1 cup whipped
topping into cream cheese mixture.
Spread evenly on cooled
crust.
Sprinkle
with
coconut.
Blend
pudding mixture, extracts and
milk.
Beat 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Spread
over
coconut
layer
and top with banana. Spread remaining
whipped topping over bananas.
Sprinkle with remaining half of nuts and chill.
Serves 15.

title: soap dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese and pour salad dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until fork can be easily inserted into chicken.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: stuffed ribs
directions: Boil ribs 10 minutes. Save broth. Cut bread into little pieces. Bake everything in pan, covered with aluminum foil. Add 1/2 cup broth. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve and enjoy!!!

title: best-ever tuna salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna into bowl.
Chop 1 tomato, 1/4 head lettuce, onion and celery into bowl.
Mix well.
Add just enough mayo to moisten.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together thoroughly the shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in applesauce and sift together flour, soda and spices and stir in.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: stained glass fruit salad
directions: Combine pudding mix with pineapple juice.
Add almond extract. Stir until thick.
Add all fruit.
Mix until fruit is well coated.

title: mexican salsa chilli dish
directions: Pat out cream cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer out in order the chilli and picante sauce.
Then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Put in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix onion powder, soup, eggs, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Add to cooked broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put a layer of cracker crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Measure flour by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt; blend together. Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick; cut with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: oriental treasure cookies(chinese)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In a large bowl, combine the remaining cookie dough ingredients.
Blend well.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix. Heat and stir until thickened on medium heat.
Remove from stove and 2 Tbsp. butter plus 1 tsp. vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue of 4 egg whites beaten until stiff and forms peak.
Add 8 Tbsp. sugar, 1 Tbsp. at a time and continue to beat.
Add pinch of salt, and 1 tsp. vanilla and stir.
Spread on top of butterscotch filling.
Bake 350° until meringue is golden brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots, onion and green pepper until tender.
Set aside. Cook tomato soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard and Worcestershire sauce for 15 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Serve cold.
This recipe keeps for about 2 weeks if kept cold.

title: apple spice bread(makes one loaf)
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Mix sugar with oil in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Add flour mixture and stir until mixed.
Grease bread pan and line just the bottom with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes.

title: cinnamon-pull-apart
directions: Scald milk, stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt and butter; let cool. Measure water in large bowl, sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour until well blended.
(May need to add 1/2 cup more flour so dough is not so sticky.)
Cover bowl and let rise until double.
Combine remaining sugar, cinnamon and pecans, if used, and set aside.
Punch down dough and place on lightly floured board.
Knead in just enough extra flour to make dough easy to handle.
Make 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip balls in melted butter and then into sugar mixture.
Brush ring pan with melted butter and add balls.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool about 10 minutes then turn out of pan.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Stir in mini chocolate chips.
Spoon into crust. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook in pan sprayed with Pam at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Stir until soft curd is well dissolved and distributed. Stir in orange juice, lemon juice, grated peel, carrot and oranges.
Mix well and chill.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put ingredients in a crock-pot or large pan; heat on low until hot.

title: buttermilk "custard" pie
directions: Combine and pour into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops to taste.
Place pineapple on chops. Put cherries on middle of pineapple.
Pour some pineapple juice on chops.
Bake at 400° to 450° until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil. Drain on paper towel.
Saute onion and peppers.
Combine last 6 ingredients in roasting pan.
Stir in peppers and onions.
Add pork chops.
Spoon liquid over chops.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: roast turkey
directions: Defrost time:
A 20 pound bird takes 3 days in refrigerator or 12 hours in sink of water.
Remove giblets as soon as thawed. Roast time:
Unstuffed, chilled turkey at 325° for 16 to 20 pounds is 4 to 6 hours; 20 to 26 pounds, 5 1/2 to 7 1/2 hours.
Baste turkey frequently with melted butter and pan juices during cooking time.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve while chilled.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Cut pickles into 1/2-inch slices, then quarter.
Return to jar.
Cook sugar, vinegar and pickling spices to boiling; boil for 1 minute.
Cool liquid slightly.
Strain and pour over pickles. Store in refrigerator for one week.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: In a heavy, high walled chicken fryer over medium heat, brown the chicken in the oil, stirring so the chicken won't stick.
When chicken is browned, remove from pot.
Add the onions, bell pepper, parsley and green onions.
Saute until the onions are clear.
Stir in the sausage, rice, stock, garlic, chicken, salt and pepper. Continue cooking until nearly all the water has boiled out, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and let simmer until the rice is done, about 1 hour.
Do not lift the lid for at least 1 hour.

title: easy cinnamon logs
directions: Cream softened oleo and 1/3 cup sugar.	Mix flour, salt and vanilla into creamed mixture.
Shape dough into logs.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 17 minutes or until
edges
are light brown.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture while still warm.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cover with enough boiling water to cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Put in colander and drain.
Heat vinegar and sugar to boiling.
Add mixture and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: tang delight
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and orange. Add juice to pudding mix and Tang. Beat 3 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour over tossed fruit.
Chill before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce with chicken
directions: In a large pot, mix everything together and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer and cook for 2 hours.
Then add chicken and cook another 2 to 3 hours or until sauce thickens.
Do not cover.
You can add more water if sauce gets too thick.

title: green bean bake(makes 48 portions)
directions: Drain beans well.
Blend soup, milk, 2 1/2 cans onions, soy sauce and pepper.
Heat.
Combine soup mixture with green beans and pour into baking pans (12 x 20 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine in
3-quart
saucepan.
Saute
broccoli, onion and garlic until tender.
Blend
in
flour,
mustard and salt. Gradually add milk and broth and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce
heat to low and blend in cheese, stirring until smooth.
Do not let this boil. Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: masquerade coconut cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields about 2 dozen cookies.

title: oh henry bars(12 servings)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; press onto a cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°; let cool.
Melt the chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Spread this mixture over the baked crust. Refrigerate until chocolate mixture is firm.
Cut into bars; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: red clam chowder
directions: Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat slightly the eggs and milk.
Mix and stir in sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter.

title: party crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir every 15 minutes for about 1 hour. Let crackers sit overnight before eating.

title: crispix cereal mix
directions: Melt the white chocolate.
Pour over cereal mixture and stir until all pieces are coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Break apart and store in an airtight container.

title: eggplant parmigiana casserole
directions: Salt eggplant; dip in milk.
Coat in flour.
Brush with salad oil.
Cook in hot oven on cookie sheet until golden.
In dish, layer eggplant slices, tomato sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Blend in butter flavor Crisco with pastry blender, knives and forks until mixture resembles pebbles. Cover and refrigerate.
When needed, 1 1/2 cups for single crust, 2 1/2 cups for double crust.
Moisten with Sprite or 7-Up to hold together.
Roll out on floured board.
Proceed with favorite pie.

title: sour cream corn
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter and add flour, salt, pepper and mix well.
Add water; cook until thick.
Stir in sour cream; add corn and cook 5 or 10 minutes on low heat.
Can be reheated.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until done.
Line bottom of dish (oblong casserole dish works best) with deboned chicken. Cover with soup. Sprinkle with a thin layer of cheese, then add a thin layer of bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° to 350° until heated.

title: hot and spicy seasoning
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in airtight container. Makes about 1/3 cup.

title: brown sugar syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and lima beans until almost tender.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Spoon over drained vegetables.
Brown cereal in butter.
Put on top.
Bake in oblong dish, uncovered.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and dip onion slices in batter. Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour into a small saucepan. Cook sauce over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: cape cod oatmeal cookies(the fannie farmer cookbook)
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in egg, sugar, butter, lard, molasses, milk, oatmeal and raisins.
Arrange on cookie sheets by teaspoonfuls.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: cherry angel cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and extract and mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread half the cream mixture over the cake slices; top evenly with one can cherry filling.
Top with remaining cake slices, cream mixture and cherry filling.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Cut into squares to serve.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Brown garlic in oil; drain oil, then add remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Saute until tender, then add tomatoes and simmer.
Even better the second day.

title: strawberry slushy
directions: Blend ingredients all together in blender.
Great for a hot summer day.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Put in casserole dish. Spread 2 cans of soup over top of meat.
Cover with cheese, then Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are brown.

title: chicken mandarin
directions: Place chicken in large shallow pan. Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours turning occasionally to coat chicken. Remove chicken from marinade. Boil marinade for a minute or so. Cover chicken with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 60-90 minutes. Baste occasionally with marinade.

title: strawberry gelato
directions: Wash strawberries and pass them through a sieve.
Add lemon juice and orange juice.
Combine sugar and water in small saucepan.
Cook until syrupy.
Cool and add to fruit mixture. Place in freezer and freeze for 1 hour or until it has consistency of thick mush.
Serves 6.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine meat (brown ground beef first and drain), celery, celery tops, bay leaves, onion, salt, hot sauce and Liquid Smoke in large stockpot.
Cook uncovered 15 minutes.
Reduce heat; cook 1 hour.
Remove chicken from broth.
Discard bay leaves and celery tops.
Cool chicken and debone; chop meat.
Add onion, tomato, potatoes and celery.
Cook 15 minutes, then simmer 1 hour on reduced heat.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer uncovered for 2 hours stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Omit salt.
Drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli in 10 x 6 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine soup and cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayo and egg to soup mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Fill a buttered quiche dish or large glass pie plate with the ham, mushrooms and onions.
In blender, blend for 30 seconds to 1 minute:
eggs, milk, Bisquick, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle top with the cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Do
not
add
salt!
Cook and slice chicken into little pieces.
Heat
soup on low.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Add chicken
to mixture.
Put cooked noodles into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch
dish.
Pour
chicken and cheese mixture over noodles. Heat in 350° oven until it bubbles.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken breast in Dutch oven. Save broth. Chop chicken into bite size pieces. Return to broth. Add cream of chicken soup and sliced carrots. Cook until carrots are tender. Add salt & pepper to taste. Bring to boil and add noodles. Cook until noodles are done.

title: green chicken enchiladas
directions: Place spinach in blender with chicken broth and blend until pureed.
Pour spinach mixture into large pan and add garlic, mushroom soup, chilies, flour, 1/2 the onion, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 the mushrooms.
Bring to a boil and turn off.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Boil prepared peppers in salted water about 5 minutes; drain. (For crisp peppers, omit the precooking.)
Sprinkle inside of pepper cups with salt.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Saut okra in fat, stirring constantly about 10 minutes or until okra appears dry.
Add onions, celery, garlic, salt, pepper and chicken to okra mixture.
Add water, tomatoes and bay leaves. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: elaine's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potato stuffing bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
In large saucepan, heat water and margarine to boiling.
Remove from heat; add milk and potato flakes, stirring until well combined.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups of the croutons, celery, onions and hot pepper sauce. Spoon into prepared casserole.
Crush remaining croutons; sprinkle around edge of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Arrange cheese slices down center of potato mixture; return to oven and bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is slightly melted.

title: coconut pound cake with sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and butter flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. (Use high speed with electric mixer.)
Sift flour and salt together, then add slowly.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into 10-inch stem pan that has been well greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
With a pastry brush, spread the softened butter over the inside surfaces of a medium-sized 12-cup muffin tin (each cup should be about 2-inches across the top).

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 350°until partially cooked.
Saute onion and tomatoes in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray until onion is tender.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper; mix well. Spoon into pie shell.
Combine mayonnaise and cheeses in bowl; mix well.
Spread over filling; sprinkle with basil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: dan's favorite french apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, spice and lemon juice; turn into a 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400 degrees until browned.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well; add vanilla and syrup.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for about 3 minutes.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar and butter; stir well.
Stir in milk, egg yolks, vanilla and nutmeg; set aside.
Beat the egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed of electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Fold beaten egg whites into sweet potato mixture.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces and boil until done.
Reserve broth for the 2 cups needed.
Place cooked chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan and add the 2 cups of water, broth and soup.
Mix flour, oleo, buttermilk, pepper and salt.
Spoon onto chicken and spread out.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: maurice's upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Beat cream cheese and margarine and add powdered sugar.
Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Put nuts and coconut in bottom of pan. Pour batter over, then drop by spoonfuls the cream cheese mix over the
top.
Do not spread. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into a large dish and mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Slice mushrooms and saute in margarine.
Grate Swiss cheese, then place on the bottom of each pie shell.
In bowl, mix eggs, flour, salt, milk and nutmeg and beat.
Pour over cheese and add sauteed mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Add Bac*Os.

title: pinto bean dumplings
directions: Put beans in kettle; add water, salt and butter or margarine. Let boil until soupy.
Put biscuits in half one at a time.
Cook 8 or 10 minutes.
Mix milk and cornstarch together well.
Let simmer 5 or 10 minutes.

title: tarragon dressing
directions: Whisk together the lemon juice, mustard, olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add tarragon and blend well.

title: beef and cheese tortilla casserole
directions: Brown beef, add onion and saute 3 minutes.
Pour off grease. Stir in coffee, salt, pepper, chili powder and 1 can tomato sauce. Heat to simmering.
Spread each tortilla with cream cheese. Place about 1/2 cup of meat mixture over cheese on half of each tortilla.
Arrange with folded edge up in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Pour remaining meat in spaces around tortillas.
Pour remaining can of sauce and water over top.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: green chili rice
directions: Cook and cool rice.
Mix together with sour cream.
Spread half of the mixture in a buttered casserole (fits well in a 1 1/2-quart Corning).
Spread cubed cheese and chilies on rice. Cover with the remaining rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.
Cook
over low heat for about 12 minutes or until thick enough to spread.

title: lloyd's creamy sweet onions
directions: Place the onions in a large bowl. In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a boil. Pour over onions. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Drain onions, discarding liquid. In a bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, celery seed, salt and pepper. Mix well. Add onions and toss to coat. Yields 4 cups.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Beat the egg yolk in a small bowl.
Blend in the molasses. Add the boiling water with the baking soda dissolved in it. Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients with the shortening and work into crumbs. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 minutes longer.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg and molasses together until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well. Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: lasagna
directions: Place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, a small amount of sauce. Place 1 layer of noodles in pan.
Combine cottage cheese and egg whites.
Place on top of noodle layer, then add sauce.
Place another layer of noodles; top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Each serving contains 259 calories, 24.8 g protein, 7.2 g fat, 53 mg chol. and 332 mg sodium.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cut carrots, celery, onions, garlic and potatoes into very thin slices.
Cut tomatoes in wedges.
Fill baking dish with vegetables, bouillon and seasonings.
Cover; bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove cover.
Bake 15 more minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with butter and arrange cream cheese over the bottom.
Meanwhile, spread chilies on paper towel to drain thoroughly.
If whole chilies are used, chip coarsely.
Combine eggs, cream, and seasonings; beat until blended.
Sprinkle chilies over cream cheese in pie shell and top with shredded cheese.
Pour egg mixture evenly over all.
Bake in preheated 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 - 10 minutes before cutting.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Chill.
Take out of refrigerator and form into small balls.
Place on long biscuit pan.
Cook in oven at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: daddy's fried chicken
directions: In bowl, mix eggs and buttermilk.
Dip chicken and roll in flour.
Cook until golden brown.

title: all american chili
directions: Cook ground beef in 2 to 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat until no longer pink, stirring often.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and chili seasoning.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir chili before serving.
Top with cheese and onion.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cami's party dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Hollow out a loaf of French or Italian bread.
Spoon mixture into hollow loaf.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.

title: 7 layer lettuce salad
directions: Make layers.
Spread mayonnaise on top and sprinkle bacon on top.
Add cheese, if desired.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add bread or rice and all the seasonings.
Add oysters, stock and giblets.
Mix and heat thoroughly, then add eggs and mix well.
Makes enough to stuff a 10-pound turkey.

title: magic cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Keep corn hot and crisp in low oven.
Cook sugar, water, salt and corn syrup to very hard ball stage (250°).
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Cook to light crack stage (270°).
Color syrup red with food coloring.
Pour over popped corn; stir well to coat every kernel.
Now press sticky popcorn into an angel food cake pan.
Do not cram, just press down firmly.
When cake is cooled, remove from pan.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and wrap chicken up in rolls.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup with chicken broth and add dry onion soup mix.
Pour over rolls and bake at 375° until rolls are golden brown.

title: pecan bread pudding
directions: Put egg white in glass measuring cup.
Add enough liquid egg substitute to make 1/2 cup.
Beat with wire whisk until mixture is well blended.
In large bowl, combine undiluted evaporated milk, nonfat milk, bread cubes and pecans.
Stir until all liquid is absorbed.
In medium bowl combine egg mixture, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir into bread mixture.
Spray 1-quart casserole with nonstick spray.
Pour bread mixture into casserole.
Place 1-quart casserole inside larger one and fill outer casserole
with hot water to half of the inner casserole's depth.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes or until golden brown and set.
Serve with warm rum custard sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coffee bars
directions: Combine raisins, coffee and cinnamon and set aside to cool. In large mixing bowl, beat shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stop beaters and drain liquid off raisins and add to the mixture in mixing bowl.
Beat in flour, soda and salt.
Beat until smooth. Then fold in, by hand, the raisins, pecans and vanilla.
Spread batter in a greased and floured large cookie pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: potato bud casserole
directions: Make 8 servings of instant potatoes according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put several pats of butter on top; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made a day ahead and refrigerated, but then will need to be heated approximately 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cut the bacon and cook in pan.
Leave grease in pan.
On low heat, add the mustard and the brown sugar.
Blend into the grease. Blend vinegar into the mixture.
Blend oil into the mixture. Bring to a slow boil; blend until thick.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl make pudding following directions on package. Add sweetened condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Stir up and set aside. Peel and slice bananas.

title: fried okra and potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Heat oil and add 1/2 mixture at a time.
Fry until crisp at medium heat; drain.

title: crazy kukes
directions: Cut out bread circles with cookie cutter.
Spread bread lightly with mayonnaise.
Top with slice of cucumber.
Just before serving, sprinkle lightly with Jane's Krazy Mixed-Up salt.

title: microwave diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Pour batter into well-greased tube dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on Low for 10 minutes and then on High for 9 to 10 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center is clean.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Brown on one side, then turn and brown on the other side.
Serve while hot.

title: tarte aux framboises
directions: Melt jelly with 4 tablespoons hot water; stir only until jelly is melted.
Cover bottom of baked pie crust with sponge cake. Pour 1/2 of berries on sponge cake.
Pour in whipped cream. Arrange remainder of berries on top of cream.
Pour melted jelly over berries to glaze.

title: millie's wacky cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Level it and make 3 holes.
Pour vinegar in one hole, vanilla in one hole and oil in last hole.
Pour water over and mix thoroughly with fork and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges.
Mix jello and cool whip.
Add marshmallows to thicken as desired.
Add cottage cheese and mandarin oranges.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix softened Cool Whip and cottage cheese well.
Add drained crushed pineapple, mashed mandarin oranges and jello gelatin.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream crisco and sugar, add eggs.
Mix soda into sour cream and add flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Drop spoon fulls on well greased pan.
Press flat with bottom of a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Sprinkle top of each cookie with sugar, cinnamon and nuts mixed together.
Bake 375 about 10 - 12 minutes.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Add salt and margarine.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites and spread over filling.
Bake at 400° until meringue is brown in 9-inch pie plate.

title: salted peanut bars
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in the microwave on High, about 2 minutes.
Add condensed milk, stir well.
Add marshmallows, stir well.
Pour 1/2 jar of peanuts into cake pan.
Cover with mixture. Sprinkle the rest of the peanuts over top.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add water and bouillon.
Boil to dissolves cubes.
Gradually add noodles and salt. Cook 3 minutes. Stir in cooked broccoli.
Add garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes. Reduce heat.
Add milk and cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix other ingredients together and pour into baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Top with grated cheese.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray (Pam).
Place 1/2 of potatoes in a layer in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place pork chops on potato layer.
Sprinkle with poultry seasoning.
Place remaining potatoes on pork chops. Mix soup and water together and pour over potatoes and meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste often.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: doris' date bread
directions: Mix dates, soda and hot water and let sit.
Cream together butter, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients and walnuts.
Then add date mixture to batter.
Grease 5 cans (I use soup cans but loaf pan may be used).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour amount desired over spinach leaves with bean sprouts, mushrooms and hard-boiled eggs.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar. Let stand 5 minutes. Combine buttermilk and soda, mixing well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender (or 2 forks) until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine yeast mixture and flour mixture. Stir well. Turn dough onto heavily floured surface and knead 8 times. Shape into a ball. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts 1 1/2 hours or until doubled. Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thickness on lightly floured surface. Cut 2-inch circles (or pinch off). Place rolls sides touching in 2 lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans. Cover and let rise in warm place (45 minutes or until doubled). Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until desired brownness. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: granny's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add milk slowly, mixing thoroughly. Bring to boil in double boiler. Add egg yolks and cook until very thick, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine. Cover with meringue from egg whites, separated from above egg yolks, adding 4 tablespoons sugar to egg whites. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and place in greased 2-quart casserole. Toss bread stuffing and mix with 1/3 cup melted butter. Spoon over carrots. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: beefy rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
In casserole, put 1 cup of rice on bottom, then hamburger, onion and green pepper on top of the rice.
Pour consomme and mushroom soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave for 40 minutes in covered casserole.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Add chicken, stirring to coat.
Heat oil in electric skillet to 375°; fry chicken until lightly browned.
Drain.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients. Blend both mixtures; beat until well mixed.
Add bananas, sour cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a buttered medium loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool before slicing.
Makes about 16 slices.

title: crusty catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut fish into thin strips; double check for bones.
In a bowl, mix 2 parts Dijon mustard and one part milk.
Salt and pepper fish; dip in mustard-milk mixture.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Place fish on a well-greased cookie sheet and bake until outside coating is crisp and the fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed corn
flakes
and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: "galatobouriko" - custard dessert with filo
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well; add farina slowly.
Put milk in large saucepan and bring to boil.
Add egg mixture slowly to milk; stir constantly until mixture boils.
Add vanilla and boil until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool.
