Stir occasionally so crust will not form.
Butter 18 x 12-inch pan. Place first sheet of filo in pan and brush with melted butter.

title: salami roll ups
directions: Spread salami slices with cream cheese. Roll around pickles. Serve.

title: alaska sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, place margarine and water; bring to a boil.
Pour mixture into a bowl with sugar, flour and salt.
Blend in with a mixer, then add buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla, along with the eggs.
When all ingredients are blended, pour into a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread with frosting while still a bit warm.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.

title: aunt marie's unbeatables
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and egg whites.
Add nuts and apricots.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Old German recipe.

title: corn biscuits
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix corn and Bisquick; drop by spoon in melted margarine.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine together cake mix, sour cream, oil and eggs; mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle over batter.
Pour remaining batter over sugar mixture.
Bake 35-40 minutes at 350°. Mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla while cake is baking.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, punch holes all over cake with a fork and pour icing mixture over the hot cake.

title: zucchini-apple bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugars, oil and vanilla in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in zucchini, apple and pecans.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove to wire rack and cool completely.
Yield:
3 loaves.

title: coffee mousse
directions: Combine milk, sugar and coffee in pan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle gelatin over water, stirring until dissolved.
Add gelatin to milk mixture and mix well.
Pour into 4 glasses.
Chill until set.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: To greased baking dish, add rhubarb.
Smooth evenly.
Mix sugar, eggs and flour (thick) mixture.
Pour evenly over rhubarb. Add butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy stew
directions: Use a 2-quart casserole.
Place ground beef in bottom of casserole; do not brown.
Pour over the vegetables.
Blend tomato juice with salt, sugar, cornstarch or tapioca and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: salsa fogata(hot chile sauce)
directions: Remove ends from chiles and discard.
Soak in hot water to soften.
Place in blender or food processor, along with 1 cup tomato juice, vinegar, garlic and oregano.
Process until chiles and garlic are finely chopped.
Add remaining tomato juice and blend.
Add sugar to cut acidity of tomato and salt.
Place in tightly covered jar and refrigerate.
Will keep about one week. Makes 2 1/2 cups salsa.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, bell pepper, cream cheese and 1/2 cup salsa in saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted. Spoon

1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up. Place seam side down in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Stir processed cheese spread (Velveeta) and milk in saucepan on low heat until smooth. Pour sauce over tortillas; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Pour remaining salsa over tortillas.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, including unbeaten eggs, and mix lightly together.

Form mixture into desired size of cake or croquette; do not pack firmly, but allow to be light and spongy. Roll out a package of crackers into fine crumbs (do not use prepared cracker crumbs), then pat the crumbs lightly on the crab cake and fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot with a smile.

title: no bake fudgies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil. After 3 minutes, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir well and drop quickly on wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: lima beans with ground meat
directions: Wash or soak beans; cover with water.
Add 2 tablespoons cooking oil, salt and pepper to taste.
Allow beans to cook. About 30 minutes before beans are done, brown ground meat with onions, salt and pepper in another skillet.
Drain and spoon them into pot of beans.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice with corn bread.

title: chicken salad
directions: Stir ingredients, mixing well.
For each portion, fill 1/2 cantaloupe with chicken salad.
Serve with Melba toast.

title: orange dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions; remove from oven and immediately poke holes all over cake with fork.
Mix jello and boiling water and pour over hot cake; let cool.
Mix pudding with milk; add vanilla and mix with Cool Whip.
Spread over top of cake.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion an garlic in hot margarine over medium heat. When onion is tender, add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Let sauce boil for five minutes.
This sauce is great for short ribs.
Simply simmer in sauce until tender.

title: pacific chowder
directions: Cook the bacon until crisp; drain.
Return 2 tablespoons of drippings to pan.
Add the chopped onion and green pepper; cook until just tender.
Add the cream of potato soup and milk; heat just to boiling.
Drain the tuna; break into chunks.
Add with crumbled bacon.
Heat.
Dash with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, peanuts and marshmallows in bowl.
Melt almond bark in microwave on defrost (30%) for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter to melted almond bark.
Pour over other ingredients. Stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper or freezer paper.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add canned milk.
Stir in confectioners sugar.

title: double 3 ice cream
directions: Mash bananas well; add egg whites stiffly beaten.
Then add juice of lemons and oranges
and
cold water which has had the sugar dissolved into it and crushed pineapple.
This makes 1 gallon after freezing.
Pour into cups, freeze and eat.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: You will need 8 sterile pint jars.

title: pickled eggs
directions: These are very, very
good
and worth the effort.
Read the recipe and have what you need on hand before you start.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add water and mix.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together; mix thoroughly.
Add the vanilla and finish mixing.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan that has been greased and lined with waxed paper or foil which has also been greased.
Bake in a 375° oven until the roll springs back when touched lightly, about 15 minutes.
When done, turn out on a paper towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up and let cool.
When cooled, unroll and spread with your favorite jam or jelly, lemon pie filling or a pudding.
Roll up carefully and refrigerate until ready to use. Sprinkle with more powdered sugar, if desired.

title: sandy's good for you stew
directions: Brown stew beef in a skillet in the olive oil. Add garlic and saute for a couple of minutes longer. Pour into a large crock pot. Brown ground beef in the skillet. Drain and add to the crock pot. Add cabbage, carrots, celery, turnips and onions to crock pot and pour on the V-8 juice. Add red wine and red wine vinegar to the crock pot. Add enough beef bouillon to cover. Season with salt and pepper and top with bay leaves. Cook on high for 4 hours. Remove bay leaves then add zucchini and cook for another hour. Add barley and cook for 1 more hour.

title: egg custard
directions: Make crust or buy.
Beat eggs thoroughly; add sugar and mix well.
Add flour and stir; add milk and extract; beat well.
Pour into crust and bake at 300° until brown.
Make sure crust doesn't have a hole in it.
Do not overcook.
Pie should move when shaken after it is finished.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices crossways.
Chop onion and add to squash.
Precook squash and onion in water; boil for 15 minutes on stove. Drain squash.
Add to squash 1 beaten egg, salt, pepper, Cheddar cheese, butter and crushed saltines.
Mix well all ingredients and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: country pork sausage
directions: Combine seasonings and sprinkle over meat cut in cubes.
Grind meat and shape into desired patties or rolls.
Freeze in meal size portions.

title: cinnamon-raisin biscuits
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins and milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 10 times.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into 2 baked pie crusts.
Cover with whipped cream after pies have cooled.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese filling
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix. Add carrots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: weihnachtskuchen(austria christmas cake)
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients over fruits and nuts.
Pour beaten eggs over mixture; add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into loaf pans, lined with wax paper, and bake in a slow oven at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours before removing from pans.
(I use 3 small loaf pans, 7 1/2 x 4 x 2 1/4-inch.)

title: cauliflower fried in butter
directions: Cook the trimmed cauliflower in salted water until tender. Drain, cool and separate the flowerets.
Dredge with flour and fry until brown in butter.
Serve with warmed butter and finely chopped parsley and salt.

title: washington apple cake
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thick and fluffy. In separate bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Beat into eggs.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture, along with vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spread apples in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour batter over apples.
Spread to cover apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix sauce and pour over chicken in crock-pot.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours.

title: potato and corn casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange 1/2 of potatoes on bottom and salt and pepper; sprinkle half of the corn and half of the chilies over potatoes. Dot with butter; repeat layer. Pour buttermilk over it all. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (until potatoes are done). Remove from oven and top with green onion and cheese; return to oven for about 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: jello garden salad
directions: Mix jello in a 9 x 13-inch pan with hot water.
Add all ingredients and mix until all liquid is absorbed.
Let set in refrigerator before using topping.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine the chocolate chips, milk and butter. Cook and stir over medium heat until chips are melted and the mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in peanuts and marshmallows.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields: about 3 1/4 pounds.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and thoroughly stir.
Chill.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Fill cupcake pans lined with paper cups one-third full.
Top each with heaping teaspoonful of topping mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Over low heat, cook onion in butter.
Add cheese and stir until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes and put in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 8.
Use a 2-quart casserole.

title: chile con queso
directions: Cook hamburg with taco mix, following directions on back of taco mix.
Cut up Velveeta into squares and place in crock-pot on low.
Add jar of salsa to crock-pot.
Add cooked hamburg.
Melt all together.
Serve warm and use as dip or sauce over vegetables. Store in Tupperware in refrigerator and warm as needed in microwave.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly, not done and drain.
Cook rice in 2 cups water.
Saute onions in margarine.
Combine broccoli, soup, milk, rice, onions, cheese, salt and pepper in greased casserole. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet dough
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, milk, salt, sugar, butter and eggs with electric mixer.
Add flour, a little at a time, until well mixed. (When too thick for mixer, mix with hands.)

title: one of life's recipes
directions: Mix these thoroughly; add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cups of prayers and faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great height of Christian living.
After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with heat of human kindness.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cut the chicken into small pieces.
Mix the chicken with the cheeses, butter, onion and pepper.
Spread out the rolls.
Put 1 TBSP. of chicken mixture on the large end and roll up.
Roll in melted butter and then seasoned bread crumbs and sliced almonds. Pour over the top 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can cream of celery soup diluted with 1 cup chicken broth or milk.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.
The rolls can be made ahead of time and frozen without the soup mix.
Put it on when you bake them.

title: simple swiss steak
directions: Place steaks in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine in a pot, tomatoes, flour, gravy and chili sauce.
Mix well and simmer 1 minute.
Pour sauce over steaks.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes (or until steak is tender).
Serve with mashed potatoes, noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Stir together the sugars, butter and milk. Boil for 1 minute. Take off stove. Add to a bowl of the oats, peanut butter, vanilla and syrup.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook first four ingredients to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Cool.
Beat.
Pour into pan and cut into squares.
If you want white or chocolate fudge, leave out peanut butter and add another 1/2 stick butter and 1/4 cup chocolate or leave out chocolate and have white fudge.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Take half of mixture and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Reserve other half of the mixture.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter together until smooth.
When mixture has blended and is smooth, add vanilla. Place cereal into a large bowl. Pour nuts into cereal.
Pour chocolate mixture over the cereal and toss until lightly coated with chocolate.
Pour powdered sugar into mixture.
Cover top of bowl (I use Tupperware) and shake like crazy until all is coated. There you have it! Puppy Chow!
Keep in a sealed container or Ziploc freezer bags.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until cheese is melted and smooth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cook broccoli until soft; drain.
Layer
with
Velveeta cheese in casserole dish. Grind up Ritz
crackers
in	bowl.
Add
soft butter and toss until blended.
Pour over broccoli and spread.
Cooked oysters or mushrooms are optional in dish.

title: creamy spinach bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels and immediately wind 3 slices bacon to make curls while still warm.
Let cool. Crumble other slice of bacon and set aside.
Combine spinach, sour cream and soup mix; stir well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with bacon curls.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add water, salad dressing and vanilla.
Beat by hand until smooth.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast and grapes cooked in wine
directions: Shake breasts in bag containing flour, salt and pepper.
In frying pan, heat oil and add chicken, garlic, basil, marjoram, tarragon and thyme.
Cook until breasts are browned. Add grapes, white wine and broth.
Flavor with lemon or honey.
Cook, uncovered, until chicken is tender.

title: spaghetti supper
directions: Lightly brown the cut up round steak with the onions, green peppers and garlic in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Stir occasionally.
Add the mushroom soup, tomato soup and water.
Add the cooked spaghetti and cheese.
Place in a 3 quart casserole. Top with additional cheese (1/2 cup).
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at high speed about 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: middle eastern turkey meatballs
directions: Combine first eight ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 18 to 20 (1 1/4-inch) meatballs.
Coat a skillet with nonstick nonfat cooking spray and saute the meatballs 8 to 10 minutes, until no longer pink in the center.
Stir occasionally.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use as a dip with chips or spread on crackers.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in blender and mix well.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and mix.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cooked bacon or ham.
Push into the pie plate contents with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal pie(oatmeal isn't just for breakfast.)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients, then pour into two 8-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together
the eggs, sugar, salt, melted butter and corn syrup.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 375° for 40	to
50	minutes,
until
a knife comes out clean. Serve alone or	with
whipped
cream.
Serve cold or slightly warm.

title: mother's cheese apple
directions: Let cheeses sit out until soft enough to handle.
Grate and mix together with flavorings.
Mold
into
shape of apple. Roll in paprika.
Add a clean
green
leaf	at the top.
Serve sliced with crackers.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all together in baking dish & top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemonade
directions: Low calorie:
Omit sugar and add 4 to 8 envelopes sugar substitute.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough out on a round pizza pan.
Bake until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Cut strawberries into slices and mix with the glaze.
Spread on top of Cool Whip and cream cheese layer. Chill and serve with a spoonful of Cool Whip on top.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: caramel ribbon brownies
directions: Heat caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix together cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread 1/2 of the cake mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot baked crust.
Drizzle caramel mixture on top.
Spread the rest of the cake mixture on top.
Bake at 325° in glass dish or at 350° in other pans for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and put in crock-pot.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley. Add cleaned, aluminum foil wrapped potatoes.
Cook on high for 5 hours or low or 8 to 10 hours. Serve with corn, beans or green beans. May serve with Minute rice instead of potatoes,

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer in order.
Pour 1 jar salsa over top, then spread Monterey Jack cheese over top.

title: silverado taco casserole
directions: In a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, place half of the broken taco shells.
In skillet, brown beef until crumbled; drain. Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir in onion and tomato sauce.
Spoon meat mixture over shells. Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Place remaining taco chips over cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with salsa sauce.

title: turkey meat balls
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Soak bread for 10 minutes in egg-milk mixture.
Add turkey, seasonings and baking powder; mix well as mixture will be soft.
Drop spoonfuls into a small amount of heated cooking oil; brown and drain.
Place meatballs in casserole dish and add white sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for one hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place flaked tuna, soup and water in casserole dish; mix well. Add macaroni and mix. Top with cheese from dinner.
Bake.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the apples with cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix remaining items until smooth.
Grease and flour a tube pan. Place one layer batter and one layer apples, starting with batter and ending with apples on top (3 layers).
Bake approximately 2 hours at 350°.

title: caviar-egg mold(appetizer)
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Pack into small bowl lined with Saran Wrap.
Chill.
When ready to serve, unmold on serving plate. Top with sour cream (spread as though frosting a cake).
Drain a jar of caviar well; spread on top.
Serve dip with crackers.

title: whang doodles
directions: Chop onion in fat and saute. Add corned beef, mashed. Add tomato paste, water, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
Mix well, heat and serve on buns.

title: saffron rice supreme
directions: Split each almond into 2 halves.
Using mortar and pestle, crush the cumin, coriander and saffron together.
Soak the raisins in hot water for a few minutes and drain.
Saute all of these ingredients for a few minutes in the butter.
Add the cooked rice and toss to color the rice and coat each grain with butter.
Add salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
Serving Size:
8. Preparation Time:

title: arizona-champagne payne mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar; let stand in refrigerator overnight. The next day, bring to room temperature; put into a saucepan.
Add egg, sugar, salt and cornstarch; cook slowly, stirring until it boils and thickens.
Cool and add mayonnaise.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and put in buttered casserole dish.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and stir into hamburger; mix well. On a 10 x 12-inch piece of wax paper, spread hamburger mixture. Arrange slices of ham on hamburger, leaving a 1-inch border all the way around.
Spread cheese on ham; roll and seal edges and ends. Bake, seam side down, in pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Put 4 slices of Mozzarella cheese, cut in half, on loaf.
Bake for 5 minutes more at 350°.

title: chocolate coconut drop cookies(no bake)
directions: Using saucepan, cook on stove the butter, instant cocoa mix, sugar and milk.
Stir and boil about 5 minutes. Add peanut butter. Stir in and add vanilla.
Add the coconut flakes and oatmeal. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet until cool.
Store cookies.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dump the first 4 ingredients all together and beat until smooth.
Pour in well-greased Bundt pan and cook at 300° for 45 minutes.
Let cake sit 5 minutes before turning it out of pan upside down.
Mix 4x sugar, grated lemon and lemon juice together. Spoon this on the cake while it is still hot.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine lemon juice, yellow egg yolk and Eagle Brand milk. Pour into pie shell; top with Cool Whip.
Chill until served.

title: tortellini in cream sauce
directions: Cook tortellini according to package.
Cook peas.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk, butter, flour, sugar and spices. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cooked peas.
Drain tortellini and mix with sauce.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter; pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Butter the sides of pan.

title: gazpacho - summer soup
directions: Mix well, no cooking.
Chill and garnish with croutons.
Makes 4 one-cup servings.

title: rich biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork until soft dough forms.
Turn out on lightly floured board and cut with a glass.
Make dough thick.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in hot oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: old fashioned rice custard
directions: In top of double boiler, combine rice and 2 cups milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring occasionally until rice is tender and most of the milk is absorbed, about 45 minutes.
Stir in butter. Beat eggs, blend in sugar, vanilla, salt and remaining 2 cups milk.
Stir into the hot rice mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole and top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: michelle's stuffed zucchini(low-fat)
directions: Use Dutch oven with lid and a heavy plate.

title: johnny appleseed dessert
directions: Melt margarine in 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Cook apples until done in water and sugar.
Pour this cooked mixture into margarine; distribute evenly over bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: pan stuffing
directions: Cube bread.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add to soup.
Pour over bread and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Toss after baking.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk; beat well.
Add flour and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: In large bowl stir together mayonnaise, onion, vinegar, salt, pepper and eggs.
Add potatoes and celery.
Toss to coat well. Cover; refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: mama's barbecued pecans
directions: Melt butter and mix in all other ingredients.
Stir in pecans until well coated.
Put in shallow pan and place in 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Store cooled pecans in tightly sealed containers until served.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Cook asparagus in 2 cups boiling water until tender.
Drain, reserving 1 cup of water.
Put chicken broth, onion and reserved water in a pan and bring to a boil.
Add the asparagus and simmer for 5 minutes.
Put in blender and puree.
Return to pan and add half and half, salt and pepper.
Reheat.

title: bacon cheddar ranch dip
directions: Fry bacon and chop into pieces.
Mix all of the ingredients together and let stand 30 minutes to an hour before serving. Serve on crackers of your choice.
Milk can be used to obtain desired consistency if needed.

title: chicken bake
directions: Dip chicken in some buttermilk and roll in flour and place in well-buttered dish or pan with meat side down.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn over and bake 15 minutes more.
Then mix soup and remaining buttermilk and pour over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: bean and cheese quesadillas
directions: Spread refried beans evenly over 4 flour tortillas.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on each tortilla over beans.
Layer chopped tomato over cheese.
Place remaining flour tortillas on top.
Wrap each in foil and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.
Cut into quarters and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Blend well. Stir in flour and spice.
Do not beat.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Spoon batter in 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done (ovens vary so keep track after 1 hour).

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo.
In separate bowl, sift together confectioners sugar and cocoa.
Pour melted cheese into sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and then slice.
Makes 6 1/2 pounds of fudge. May be halved.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix eggs with sugar; add milk, peanut butter and cream, blending well.
Vanilla flavoring may be added if desired.
Add milk/water to fill line of 4-quart churn.

title: stuffed bass
directions: Brush fish with melted butter; sprinkle with salt & pepper to taste. Spread stuffing over fish. Top with last 3 ingredients in order given.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together mixing thoroughly.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no bake cocoa cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Take off fire and add remaining ingredients.

title: fruit cup
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces.
Add juice and mix; keep refrigerated.
Yield:
2 cups.
Carbohydrate 22 g, protein 1 g, fat .4 g, calories 92.
One serving (1/2 cup) = 2 fruit exchanges.

title: potato filling
directions: Mash the potatoes, adding 1/2 cup warm milk and beating until fluffy. Chop finely the onion and celery and saute in butter.
Add bread cubes after browned. Add chopped parsley. Add the egg and salt and pepper to taste. Add potatoes.
Put in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole. Cover with cooked chicken.
Pour mixture of chicken soup and mayonnaise over all.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Prepare herb dressing mix as directed on package and cover the layer of cheese.
Bake at 300° until brown and bubbly, about 1 hour.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add all ingredients to brown onion. Mix and add to beef and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: 3 things
directions: In skillet, scramble hamburg and onion and cook over medium heat until done.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt together in double boiler chocolate and sugar. Add salt, light corn syrup, cornstarch and milk.
Cook for 15 minutes, while stirring until it thickens.
Add butter.
Cool. Add brandy or vanilla.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, dill, salt and pepper.
Add to macaroni, tomatoes, cucumbers and onions.
Toss to coat well. Chill.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Mix all together.
Grind lemon peel, orange peel and citron peel.
Then add to mixture and let set overnight before baking. It is very stiff dough.
Roll out and bake at 350°.

title: incredible butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: french-style green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook until butter melts, stirring constantly. Add sour cream.
Drain green beans; then add.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese and crackers.
Sprinkle butter over top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: broccoli puff
directions: For grilled dinners or picnics, try carrots baked in foil.

title: orange sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Add orange peel and orange juice.
Beat until very thick.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Fold in flour a little at a time.
Beat egg whites with the cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar beating until soft peaks form. Thoroughly fold whites into yolk mixture.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan in slow oven (325°) about 55 minutes or until done.
Invert pan to cool.

title: angel's cool coffee punch
directions: Combine coffee, milk, and vanilla.
Add sugar until dissolved.
Chill thoroughly and pour over ice cream that has been spooned into a punch bowl.
Serves approximately 25 punch cups.

title: shapleigh luncheon cheese
directions: Spread bread with margarine.
Cut each slice into 8 strips. Put a layer in buttered baking dish.
Arrange the rest of the strips, upright, around the sides of dish.
Mix slightly beaten eggs, cream, salt, mustard, paprika and cheese; pour into dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable dilly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Best if made ahead of time for flavor to set in.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack in a loaf pan firmly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Stir flour and sugar together.
Cut in shortening until size of peas.
Mix buttermilk with yeast water.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until moistened.
May be covered and refrigerated overnight.

title: teatime tassies
directions: Cheese Pastry:
Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften at room temperature.
Blend.
Stir in flour.
Chill slightly, about 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased muffin cups.
Press dough on bottom and sides of cup.

title: recipe for a happy life
directions: Mix thoroughly and add tears of joy and sorrow with sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cups of prayers and faith to lighten other ingredients and raise texture to a great height of Christian living.
After pouring all this into your daily life, bake with the heat of human kindness and serve with a smile that reflects wonders from above.
Serves all.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Pour cooked spaghetti into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over spaghetti and toss together.
Spread 1 quart spaghetti sauce over mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
Add topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine 4 tablespoons of oleo, salt, paprika and flour; blend until smooth.
Add milk gradually; stir until thickened.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Saute onion and celery in 1 tablespoon of oleo.
Add to soup mixture and add eggs. Alternate layers of asparagus and sauce in 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
If not
moist,
add 1 teaspoon water at a time until right consistency.
Make small balls 1-inch in diameter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: delightful trifle
directions: Break cake into small pieces and line bottom and sides of a tube pan.
Mix pudding and milk according to box.
Mix pineapple in pudding and pour into cake pan.
Spread evenly and press into the cake.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Turn cake onto plate and ice top and sides with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with cherries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes and onion in a 4-quart saucepan. Cover with about 6 cups of water, butter, salt and pepper to taste. Cook until potatoes are done (about 15 to 20 minutes). Drain water until potatoes are just covered. Add milk and soups. Heat should be very low at this point. Cook only until thoroughly heated. Garnish with bacon and cheese.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Wheat Thins.
Prepare entire box of crackers this way.
Melt chocolate and dip prepared crackers.
Cool and serve.

title: rice-broccoli bake
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Heat soup, milk and cheese.
Add onion, rice and broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: black bottom strawberry pie
directions: In small bowl, combine first 4 ingredients until smooth; spread into crust.
Chill while preparing filling.
In medium bowl, combine pudding mix and milk with electric mixer; beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping and coconut; spread over chocolate.
Spread remaining topping over pudding.
Cover and freeze until firm but not frozen.
To serve, hull strawberries and cut in half.
Arrange berries on top of pie. Makes 8 servings.

title: connemara chicken
directions: Pour 3 tablespoons oil in a skillet and 1 minced garlic clove, brown, then add cut-up chicken.
Brown on all sides over moderate heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
You have a real good gravy and can serve spaghetti on the side.

title: mushroom alfredo sauce
directions: While cooking pasta to desired doneness, melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Gradually stir in half and half, water and chicken bouillon cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Add sliced drained mushrooms and Parmesan and heat until melted.
Serve over hot pasta.
Serves 4.

title: chess pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Pour in a cooked pie crust. Top with meringue and cook at 300° until brown.

title: mediterranean fish soup
directions: *Can substitute some shrimp, medium size, peeled and deveined if desired.

title: mom's favorite doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add and beat in sugar and melted butter.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add to egg-buttermilk mixture.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Roll dough to about 1/3 inch thick.
Cut and fry.

title: fantastic cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese and eggs together.
Add 2/3 cup of sugar and almond extract; mix well.
Bake in a greased pie pan or pie dish at 325° for 50 minutes.
Take out of oven and cool for 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
In a large bowl, layer sliced bananas, wafers, pudding and sour cream.
If you have time, refrigerate overnight so flavors can blend.

title: caribbean cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust (in deep pie plate), and set aside.
Toast 3/4 cup packed coconut in 350° oven.
Watch closely and remove from oven when light brown.
Set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and taco seasoning mix. Spread on 2 round pizza pans (like a pizza crust).
Cover with salsa (pizza sauce) and add toppings.
Serve with taco chips and corn chips.

title: chili-roll
directions: To get a really good start, plant your own cucumbers in early spring. For the best pickles, plant National Pickling Cucumbers. Tend them carefully, keeping them moist and insect free. Don't let them get too large. Gather the cucumbers early in the day, before the sun gets to them. Use cucumbers from 3 to 4-inches long and about 3/4-inch diameter. Start your preparation immediately. If you must wait, wash the cucumbers and put them in ice water until you are ready.

title: vanilla torte
directions: Combine and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: water chestnuts wrapped in bacon
directions: Marinate first 3 ingredients at least 30 minutes.
Wrap with bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Bake in 350° oven until bacon is done or in microwave until bacon is done.

title: barbecue salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients, but salmon, and shake well.
Place salmon on rack in shallow pan, skin side down.
Baste salmon with sauce 1/2 hour before broiling.
Broil for 7 to 10 minutes until pieces just begin to flake.
Do not overbake.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening. Gradually add milk; stir to soft dough.
Roll into 1/8-inch thick rectangle on a lightly floured surface into 5-inch squares.
Place 3 or 4 pieces apple on each square; sprinkle with sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon, which have been mixed together.
Dot with butter. Moisten edges and bring corners to center; pinch edges to seal. Place dumplings 1 inch apart in lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Heat remaining sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, hot water and margarine and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over dumplings. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
1 dozen dumplings.

title: california marinated mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms well under running water; remove stems and drain caps.
Combine Burgundy with oil and garlic salt; pour over mushrooms and allow to marinate several hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.
Serve on cocktail picks.
Mushrooms will darken slightly, but are delicious!

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix water with Bisquick.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured surface.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into 13-inch circle.
Cut circle into 8 wedges.
Place frankfurter on each wedge.
Roll up beginning at wide end.
Seal tightly by pinching point into roll.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken, green beans and rice(low calorie and fat)
directions: Cook chicken ahead and cut up.
Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.

(**For broth, use liquid from cooking chicken and use liquid drained from green beans and mushrooms; if more is needed, add water and a small amount of chicken base for 13 3/4 ounces.) Bring to a boil; stir in rice.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet mixed relish
directions: Put cabbage, tomatoes, celery and peppers through food grinder.
Combine vegetables, mustard seed, celery seed and salt in a large saucepan.
Add vinegar and sugar; cook slowly for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add more sugar if you want a sweeter relish.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: zucchini and potatoes
directions: Cut unpeeled potatoes and zucchini into 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add potatoes.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour in chicken broth.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add onion, zucchini, tomato and seasonings.
Stir.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients in large container.
Mix well.
Press in loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before cutting. Keep refrigerated.

title: pig in a pinwheel(luncheon savories)
directions: Mash the ham, onion and oregano into the cream cheese. Unroll dough which is perforated into 16 triangles.
Separate it into eight rectangles instead, then squish the central perforations to seal.
Spread an equal amount of the ham and cheese mixture over each rectangle.
Roll up each rectangle, starting at the short side.
Cut each into four slices.
Place on cookie sheet and squish down slightly.
Bake at 375°F or 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 32 pinwheels.

title: banana-blueberry bread
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in banana.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring gently.
Add blueberries to mixture.
Stir just enough to mix.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick is inserted in center and comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: cabbage fry plus
directions: Saute onions in oil in large skillet over medium heat until light brown, about 8 minutes.
Stir in cabbage, celery, carrots, green pepper and mushrooms.
Saute for 2 minutes; sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix gently.
Spoon tomatoes on top of vegetables.
Cook, covered, over low heat, just until vegetables are crisp-tender, 6 to 8 minutes.

title: waldorf salad with chicken
directions: Combine preserves, mayonnaise, chives, mustard, lemon juice, salt and pepper in large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Add chicken, apples, celery, raisins and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange lettuce leaves on plate.
Mound salad on lettuce.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.
